or. It is particularly designed for high-velocity, deep-hole drilling and boring of all nonferrous metals. In addition, it is suggested for general machining of free-machining alloys, magnesium, and free-machining brass, bronze, and phosphor bronze, as well as high-speed, light-feed machining of screw stock steels. Moreover, it can be utilized as a lubricant for high-speed spindles.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"APPLICATIONS\",\"bold\":true}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"ATLANTIC NEAT CUTTING OIL 3 is primarily designed for fast, deep-hole drilling and boring of all nonferrous metals. In addition, it is suggested for general machining of free-machining alloys, magnesium, and free-machining brass, bronze, and phosphor bronze, as well as high-speed, light-feed machining of screw stock steels.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"PRODUCT FEATURES & BENEFITS\",\"bold\":true}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Outstanding machining abilities\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Multifunctional applications\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Reduced misting propensity\"}]}]','2024-08-17 07:34:26.603000','2024-08-31 07:30:27.158000','2024-08-17 07:34:29.199000',2,2,'1,4,5,20,25,208','NCO-3',NULL,NULL,'ATLANTIC NEAT CUTTING OILS'),(23,'ATLANTIC SOLUBLE CUTTING FLUIDS','atlantic-soluble-cutting-fluids','[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"ATLANTIC SOLUBLE CUTTING OIL is a long-life, biostable, chlorine-free high-performance metal working fluid. When mixed with water the emulsion formed has a milky appearance. It is formulated with high levels of lubricity additives to provide excellent performance in arduous machining operations.\"}]},{\"type\":\"heading\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"PRODUCT FEATURES & BENEFITS\"}],\"level\":2},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"ATLANTIC SOLUBLE CUTTING OIL is a high-performance, chlorine-free product suitable for machining a wide range of metals. It provides the flexibility for product rationalization and is particularly suitable for machining aluminum alloys used in the automotive industry. It is formulated to provide long service life and to resist bacterial growth to help reduce smells associated with bacterial degradation.Outstanding machining performance on aluminum, non-ferrous metals and ferrous metals, including stainless steels. Wide multi-metal machining range. Stable in a wide range of diluent water qualities. Oil content protects machined components, machine fittings and fixtures. Highly resistant to bacterial degradation.\"}]},{\"type\":\"heading\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"APPLICATIONS\"}],\"level\":2},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"ATLANTIC SOLUBLE CUTTING OIL is recommended for machining aluminum, steels and yellow metals. It can be used in individual machine sumps and in centralized coolant systems.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Recommended dilutions for Turning, Drilling, Sawing, Milling, Reaming, Deep Hole Boring: 5-10%.\"}]}]','2024-08-17 07:47:02.316000','2024-08-31 07:31:26.224000','2024-08-17 07:47:06.469000',2,2,'1,4,5,20,25,208',NULL,NULL,NULL,'ATLANTIC SOLUBLE CUTTING FLUIDS'),(24,'ATLANTIC TRUNK PISTON ENGINE OIL-1','atlantic-trunk-piston-engine-oil-1','[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"ATLANTIC TRUNK PISTON ENGINE OIL is a multi-functional crankcase lubricant that is specially formulated to help reduce deposits in critical areas (such as the piston under crown) and gives long-term protection against corrosion of ferrous and non-ferrous metals. It is designed to be used in rated medium-speed diesel engines that run on residual fuel.\"}]},{\"type\":\"list\",\"format\":\"unordered\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"list-item\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"The \"},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"ATLANTIC TP 30\",\"bold\":true},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" and TP 40 were developed specifically for use in settings involving a moderate amount of oil stress.\"}]},{\"type\":\"list-item\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"ATLANTIC TP X 40\",\"bold\":true},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" is developed to help improve deposit control and is designed specifically for use in environments characterized by high oil stress.\"}]},{\"type\":\"list-item\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"ATLANTIC TP XL 40\",\"bold\":true},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" has been further improved to increase deposit control and is developed specifically for conditions characterized by extremely high oil stress.\"}]}]},{\"type\":\"heading\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"PROPERTIES\"}],\"level\":2},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"ATLANTIC TRUNK PISTON ENGINE OIL is a combination of highly refined base oils and an exclusive formulation of the most recent additive technologies. This combination offers a substantial safety margin to help diesel engines deal with higher stress levels, which are present in even the most recent and upcoming diesel engine designs. Especially suited for use in engines with a low or extremely low oil consumption that also operates on the fuel of a low-quality residual.\"}]},{\"type\":\"heading\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"PRODUCT BENEFITS\"}],\"level\":2},{\"type\":\"list\",\"format\":\"unordered\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"list-item\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Outstanding resistance to the detriments caused by contamination with residual fuel.\"}]},{\"type\":\"list-item\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"High thermal resistance as well as resistance to oxidation at high temperatures.\"}]},{\"type\":\"list-item\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Outstanding control of viscosity increase, which results in fewer calls for top-ups.\"}]},{\"type\":\"list-item\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Extremely good resistance to wear and very good oil film strength even when subjected to extremely high pressures.\"}]},{\"type\":\"list-item\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"A reduction in the accumulation of heavy deposits in the engine, which leads to cost savings in terms of maintenance.\"}]},{\"type\":\"list-item\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Good engine cleanliness.\"}]},{\"type\":\"list-item\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Very high base number and exceptional base number preservation.\"}]},{\"type\":\"list-item\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Compatibility with centrifugal separation equipment.\"}]}]},{\"type\":\"heading\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"APPLICATIONS\"}],\"level\":2},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"ATLANTIC TRUNK PISTON ENGINE OIL is formulated to be used in the lubrication of medium-speed industrial or marine propulsion and auxiliary engines that burn residual fuel oils, as well as some medium and high-speed engines that burn distillate fuel, in situations where a high Base Number, high ash lubricant is suitable. These engines can be found in both land-based and marine environments. Compatible with bearings and stern tubes, as well as the lubrication of reduction gears.\"}]},{\"type\":\"heading\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"RECOMMENDATIONS\"}],\"level\":2},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"The API service goes above and beyond the CF specification.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"The quality criteria of all major medium-speed engine manufacturers, including WRTSIL, MAN diesel, Caterpillar MaK, Yanmar, Daihatsu, HiMSEN, and Rolls Royce, are met or exceeded by this product.\"}]}]','2024-08-19 05:26:19.997000','2025-05-16 07:15:55.826000',NULL,2,2,'200,208,1000','ENGINE OIL',NULL,NULL,'ATLANTIC TRUNK PISTON'),(25,'ATLANTIC PREMIUM PLUS 2-CYCLE OUTBOARD – 2-Stroke Engine Oil','atlantic-premium-plus-2-cycle-outboard-2-stroke-engine-oil','[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"ATLANTIC PREMIUM PLUS 2-CYCLE OUTBOARD OIL is a high-performance, 2-stroke engine oil that is developed for numerous high-performance, water-cooled 2-stroke engines that are used in outboard marine applications. These engines are engineered for high levels of performance. It features an environmentally friendly engine and excellent performance. The longevity of the product is ensured by the use of specialized base oils and an additive.\"}]},{\"type\":\"heading\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"PROPERTIES\"}],\"level\":2},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"ATLANTIC PREMIUM PLUS 2-CYCLE OUTBOARD OIL is created using purified traditional mineral oils and an ashless dispersion additive system. This combination offers superior protection against exhaust port deposits, corrosion, and wear.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Spark plug fouling and pre-ignition are both reduced, which contributes to the vehicle’s faultless running. Both newer and older 2-stroke engine models can benefit from using this product to their full potential.\"}]},{\"type\":\"heading\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"PRODUCT FEATURES AND BENEFITS\"}],\"level\":2},{\"type\":\"list\",\"format\":\"unordered\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"list-item\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Protects against the production of sludge; Does not pose a threat to marine life; Good detergent properties even when heated to high temperatures.\"}]},{\"type\":\"list-item\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"A composition that is easy to burn and ashless, which prevents pre-ignition as well as plug fouling and exhaust port clogging.\"}]},{\"type\":\"list-item\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Excellent resistance to both heat and oxidation.\"}]},{\"type\":\"list-item\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Properties that are resistant to wear and can bear a load effectively.\"}]},{\"type\":\"list-item\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Increases the amount of clean combustion and decreases the number of deposits in the combustion area.\"}]},{\"type\":\"list-item\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Excellent anti-seizure and anti-scuffing performance.\"}]},{\"type\":\"list-item\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Good dispersing characteristics.\"}]},{\"type\":\"list-item\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Good moisture tolerance.\"}]}]},{\"type\":\"heading\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"APPLICATIONS\"}],\"level\":2},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"ATLANTIC PREMIUM PLUS 2-CYCLE OUTBOARD OIL is suggested for use in two-stroke engines that were built by Johnson, Mercury, OMC, Evinrude, Mariner, Force, Mercruiser, Yamaha, Suzuki, Nissan, and Tohatsu, as well as in applications where NMMA TC-W, TC-WII, or TC-W3 lubricants are advised. It is also appropriate for use in air-cooled, two-stroke engines that are light to moderate workloads, such as those that are used in power mowers, chain saws, leaf blowers, and lawn trimmers. Depending on the recommendations provided by the manufacturer, ATLANTIC PREMIUM PLUS 2-CYCLE OUTBOARD OIL can be used at a fuel-to-oil ratio of up to 1:50.\"}]}]','2024-08-19 07:01:54.706000','2025-05-16 06:09:46.620000',NULL,2,2,'200,208,1000','2-Stroke Engine Oil',NULL,NULL,'ATLANTIC PREMIUM PLUS'),(26,'ATLANTIC OUTBOARD OIL 4T','atlantic-outboard-oil-4-t','[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"ATLANTIC OUTBOARD OIL 4T series are four-stroke engine oils for outboard applications that are made with carefully selected high-quality base oils and specific four-stroke additives. They fulfill the most recent criteria of the NMMA.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"OUTBOARD OIL 4T 10W30 is a synthetic-based engine oil designed for use in all 4-stroke gasoline engines found in pleasure craft. It offers the highest level of engine protection possible across the extensive range of operating conditions that are typical of outboard motors, which include everything from high-speed cruising to extended periods of time spent idling.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"High levels of wear protection and exceptional corrosion resistance are provided by OUTBOARD OIL 4T 25W40, which is a mineral-based, low-ash engine oil specially developed for use in 4-stroke outboard marine engines.\"}]},{\"type\":\"heading\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"PRODUCT FEATURES & BENEFITS\"}],\"level\":2},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Oil made from synthetic components, created specifically to operate in environments with high temperatures.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"A very high capacity for cleaning; the assurance of a consistent level of engine efficiency.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Superior resistance to shear force.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Excellent characteristics to prevent corrosion, ensuring the item’s protection when it is stored over the winter.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Properties that are unmatched in their resistance to rust and corrosion.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"The formulation is specifically designed to cut down on the amount of fuel used and the pollutants that cause pollution.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Increased piston cleanliness while simultaneously decreasing oil usage.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Excellent resistance to the loss of viscosity.\"}]},{\"type\":\"heading\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"APPLICATIONS\"}],\"level\":2},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"OUTBOARD OIL 4T 10W30 is the newest generation of oil that was produced for the new emissions-free 4-stroke outboard petrol engines that are used under full load. This oil is especially suggested for use in marine outboard applications.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"It is highly advised that you use OUTBOARD OIL 4T 25W40 in any and all outboard engines, even those that call for an oil that meets the ‘FC-W’ criteria. Extraordinarily well-suited for the lubrication of four-stroke outboard engines, which are frequently subjected to high speeds and the largest loads, and for use in situations containing both fresh water and salt water.\"}]},{\"type\":\"heading\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"RECOMMENDATIONS\"}],\"level\":2},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"The quality standards of NMMA FC-W and FB-00603J, as well as the requirements of API service SL and SL/CF, are satisfied by OUTBOARD OIL 4T 10W30.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"ensuring compatibility with the specifications provided by Bombardier, Evinrude, Honda, Johnson, Mercury, Sea-Doo, Suzuki, and Yamaha, among other manufacturers.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"The quality standards established by NMMA FC-W, FB-80812K have been met by OUTBOARD OIL 4T 25W40.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"In accordance with the specifications laid down by the manufacturers of Yamaha, Honda, Suzuki, Johnson/Evinrude, Tohatsu/Nissan, and Mercury Verado.\"}]}]','2024-08-19 08:07:17.800000','2025-05-16 06:09:59.881000',NULL,2,2,'200,208,1000','4T',NULL,NULL,'ATLANTIC OUTBOARD OIL'),(27,'ATLANTIC MARINOL GEN 4-1','atlantic-marinol-gen-4-1','[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"ATLANTIC MARINOL GEN 4 is a lubricant that does not contain zinc or chlorine and is made with base stocks of the highest quality. It has low consumption characteristics, high-temperature oxidation resistance, and thermal stability. When these basic stocks are mixed with carefully chosen and stable additives, the resulting engine oil has qualities that are harmoniously distributed over the spectrum.\"}]},{\"type\":\"heading\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"PROPERTIES\"}],\"level\":2},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"ATLANTIC MARINOL GEN 4 is made with base stocks of the highest quality and with additives that have been carefully chosen. They impart superior lubricating qualities, low consumption features, high-temperature oxidation resistance, and thermal stability upon the oil. It is also appropriate for use in other high-horsepower marine diesel engines that run on distillate fuels with a sulfur concentration of up to 1.5%.\"}]},{\"type\":\"heading\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"PRODUCT FEATURES AND BENEFITS\"}],\"level\":2},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Protects silver bearings; possesses excellent degreasing capabilities even when heated to high temperatures.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Possesses excellent dispersing qualities; helps prevent the production of sludge.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Acids that are created during the combustion process are neutralized.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Excellent resistance to both heat and oxidation.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Properties that are resistant to wear and can bear a load effectively.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Excellent TBN retention in addition to a high TBN content.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Containing no zinc or chlorine.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Superior resistance to water and ability to separate.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Reduces the production of carbon deposits and varnish, so extending the life of the oil and the filter.\"}]},{\"type\":\"heading\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"APPLICATIONS\"}],\"level\":2},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"ATLANTIC MARINOL GEN 4 is a marine-grade diesel fuel that has been specially developed to fulfil the prerequisites of EMD’s strongly loaded diesel engines, which are typically found in applications involving water. It is appropriate for use in other marine diesel engines that have a greater brake mean effective pressure (BMEP) and can use distillate fuels with a sulfur content of up to 1.5%. The engine must have the greatest horsepower. Also, it can lubricate engines of the kind used in drilling rigs and in the service of stationary power generation.\"}]},{\"type\":\"heading\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"RECOMMENDATIONS\"}],\"level\":2},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"The quality standards of the engines built by Alco, Detroit Diesel (API CF-2), and Fairbanks Morse are satisfied or exceeded by this product.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"ATLANTIC MARINOL GEN 4 satisfies the criteria for an SAE 40 grade marine diesel engine oil, is appropriate for use wherever API CF and/or CF-2 performance is required and is rated as an LMOA Generation 4 lubricant. These requirements allow it to be used wherever API CF and/or CF-2 performance is specified.\"}]}]','2024-08-19 08:30:02.675000','2025-05-26 12:03:36.217000','2025-05-22 12:54:42.983000',2,4,'200,208,1000',NULL,NULL,NULL,'ATLANTIC MARINOL GEN 4'),(28,'ATLANTIC MARINOL – Diesel Engine Oil','atlantic-marinol-diesel-engine-oil','[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"The engine oils in the \"},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"ATLANTIC MARINOL\",\"bold\":true},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" range are designed for high-speed diesel vehicles and come highly recommended for the lubrication of turbo-charged vehicles that operate in extremely demanding environments.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"ATLANTIC MARINOL ‘S’\",\"bold\":true},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" are high-performance mono-grade diesel engine oils that are developed for the highest output, high-speed diesel engines that use distillate fuel. Their formulation is meant to deliver better engine protection and longer drain intervals than regular diesel engine oils. They are particularly well suited for the high power-to-weight ratio units that are utilised in swift watercraft and small generator sets.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"ATLANTIC MARINOL ‘W’\",\"bold\":true},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" is a high-performance, multifunctional diesel engine lubricant designed for use in all modern high-speed (>1200rpm) diesel engines that burn distillate fuels with a sulfur content of up to 1% wt. ATLANTIC MARINOL ‘W’ is a high-performance, multifunctional diesel engine lubricant designed for use in all modern high-speed (>1200rpm) diesel engines.\"}]},{\"type\":\"heading\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"PRODUCT FEATURES & BENEFITS\"}],\"level\":2},{\"type\":\"heading\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"ATLANTIC MARINOL ‘S’\"}],\"level\":3},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Longer oil drain intervals.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Superb detergent and dispersion capabilities, ensure that the engine will remain clean under any and all operating situations.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Excellent resistance to both corrosion and oxidation, which contributes to the engine’s long-term reliability.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"High resistance to wear and ability to withstand strong pressure make this material suitable for use in reduction gears.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Superior defence against the practise of bore polishing.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Very spotless condition of the pistons.\"}]},{\"type\":\"heading\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"ATLANTIC MARINOL ‘W’\"}],\"level\":3},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"The lubricant has a very stable multigrade property, which enables it to be used throughout the year.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"When the engine is cold, starting it is less of a struggle.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Extremely high detergent qualities even when heated to very high levels.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Very high levels of dispersant activity despite the low temperature.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Outstanding resistance to thermal instability.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"High oxidation resistance.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Excellent resistance to wear and tear qualities.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Maximize the engine’s service life.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Extended Oil Life.\"}]},{\"type\":\"heading\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"APPLICATIONS\"}],\"level\":3},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"ATLANTIC MARINOL ‘S’ was developed to fulfill the specifications of high-speed diesel engines that run on distillate fuels.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Reduction gears, torque converters, and stern tubes can all benefit from this material.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"ATLANTIC MARINOL ‘W’ is highly recommended for use in the lubrication of high-speed propulsion engines, such as those found in coastal vessels, fishing trawlers, rescue boats, lifeboats, emergency power units, fire pumps (in accordance with IMO international safety rules), and high-speed engine generators operating in cold environments.\"}]},{\"type\":\"heading\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"RECOMMENDATIONS\"}],\"level\":2},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"ATLANTIC MARINOL W meets or exceeds the quality requirements of CUMMINS CES 200-71,-72, 76, (B&C Series) CES 200-75, Mitsubishi, Perkins, Caterpillar: ECF-2, MTU MTL 5044 Category 1 / 2, Mercedes Benz 228.3, MAN 3275, Volvo VDS 2, GM Allison C-4.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"API service CI-4, CH-4, ACEA: E3-96, E5 A2-96, B3-98.\"}]}]','2024-08-19 08:47:45.400000','2025-05-16 06:10:19.555000',NULL,2,2,'200,208,1000','Diesel Engine Oil',NULL,NULL,'ATLANTIC MARINOL'),(29,'ATLANTIC MARINE SYSTEM OIL','atlantic-marine-system-oil','[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"ATLANTIC MARINE SYSTEM OIL\",\"bold\":true},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" was developed specifically for the crankcase lubrication of low-speed two-stroke crosshead diesel engines. Also, it is suited for the plain bearings of turbochargers, shaft bearings, seals, and stern tubes. The formulation possesses outstanding water separation characteristics, maximal antiwear properties, and effective rust prevention when used in the presence of salt water.\"}]},{\"type\":\"heading\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"APPLICATIONS\"}],\"level\":2},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Lubrication of the crankshaft-cooled pistons and shaft bearings are the primary function of the ATLANTIC MARINE SYSTEM OIL. It is highly recommended for use as system oil in late model, high-output, crosshead diesel engines, particularly those engines that utilize the system oil for piston cooling. It will prevent or limit the accumulation of deposits in the piston cooling spaces, which will result in the maintenance of piston cooling efficiency as well as a reduced likelihood of piston top burning and piston crown cracking. It will also prevent or decrease deposits in the crankcase, and it will give exceptional protection for bearings that are subjected to heavy loads.\"}]},{\"type\":\"heading\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"PROPERTIES\"}],\"level\":2},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"ATLANTIC MARINE SYSTEM OIL is formulated from high-quality, paraffinic base oils and a balanced additive system to provide excellent protection even for the severe operating conditions of the newest design, high-output crosshead marine diesel engines. These conditions can be attributed to the fact that ATLANTIC MARINE SYSTEM OIL is able to provide excellent protection. In addition, the alkalinity is high enough to neutralize any acidic combustion products or crankcase contaminations in a less demanding four-stroke trunk piston diesel engine that runs on distillate fuel.\"}]},{\"type\":\"heading\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"PRODUCT FEATURES AND BENEFITS\"}],\"level\":2},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Extremely high level of detergency; Very high resistance to thermal instability.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Extremely good anti-oxidant capabilities; excellent anti-rust and anti-corrosive properties; Very good anti-bacterial traits.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Outstanding control over deposits with an oil-cooled piston.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Outstanding capability for the separation of water.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"High capacity for the separation of insoluble materials.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Excellent resistance to wear and tear.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Strong resistance to the formation of foam.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Crankcase should be cleaned.\"}]},{\"type\":\"heading\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"RECOMMENDATIONS\"}],\"level\":2},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Satisfies or outperforms the quality standards set by the leading manufacturers of diesel engines.\"}]}]','2024-08-19 08:54:56.917000','2025-05-16 06:10:29.632000',NULL,2,2,'200,208,1000',NULL,NULL,NULL,'ATLANTIC MARINE SYSTEM OIL'),(30,'ATLANTIC MARINE HD – Mono-Grade Marine Diesel Engine Oil','atlantic-marine-hd-mono-grade-marine-diesel-engine-oil','[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"The ATLANTIC MARINE OIL HD line is a variety of high-performance, mono-grade marine diesel engine oils that display improved dispersancy. These oils are particularly well-suited for high BMEP medium and high-speed diesel engines that run on distillate and MDO fuels. These high-tech diesel lubricants are offered in SAE grades 30, 40, and 50, making them suitable for the viscosity requirements of the majority of marine engines. Because of the unique combination of detergent and dispersion capabilities that these oils possess, they not only offer greater resistance to the formation of lacquer in applications that subject them to rigorous service, but they also help in the removal of sludge and deposits.\"}]},{\"type\":\"heading\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"PROPERTIES\"}],\"level\":2},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"ATLANTIC MARINE OIL’s HD series of lubricants are created specifically for use in high BMEP engines and in severe-duty engine applications. These kinds of applications call for a higher level of dispersancy and liner lacquer control than is typically provided by the vast majority of diesel lubricants because of the nature of the fuel and the service. They are created using high-quality base stocks and a well-balanced additive system to guarantee the best possible performance and defense for trunk piston engines used in industrial and maritime settings where monograde oils are required.\"}]},{\"type\":\"heading\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"PRODUCT BENEFITS\"}],\"level\":2},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Longer oil drain intervals, extended cylinder overhauls, less bore polishing, superior wear protection, decreased oil consumption and decreased liner lacquering are some of the benefits of this technology.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Superior ability to separate water from other substances; optimal TBN reserves; enhanced oxidation and thermal stability.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"The cleanliness of the engine was improved, and there was less muck on the top deck.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"A broad range of engine capabilities in terms of builder, size, and speed; decreased deposits in the piston ring grooves; exceptional protection against ring and linear wear.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Superb detergent and dispersant capabilities ensure that the engine is kept clean and that the engine and transmission systems have a long lifespan.\"}]},{\"type\":\"heading\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"APPLICATIONS\"}],\"level\":2},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"The ATLANTIC MARINE OIL HD series is designed to work with the most recent generation of diesel engines, such as those manufactured by MAN-B&W Alpha, Caterpillar (3600), Deutz, and Stork Werkspoor. Due to the fact that they have an FZG rating of 12, they are fantastic severe pressure gear lubricants.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Main and auxiliary engines of all types and ratings, naturally aspirated, turbocharged, or supercharged.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Clutched reduction driver, reversing gear system, stern tubes, and bearings. Suitable for lubrication of medium and high-speed diesel engines used for fishing fleets and river transport applications.\"}]},{\"type\":\"heading\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"RECOMMENDATIONS\"}],\"level\":2},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Satisfies or outperforms the quality standards set by the leading manufacturers of diesel engines.\"}]}]','2024-08-19 09:07:47.002000','2025-05-16 06:10:47.358000',NULL,2,2,'200,208,1000','Mono-Grade Marine Diesel Engine Oil',NULL,NULL,'ATLANTIC MARINE HD'),(31,'ATLANTIC MARINE CYLINDER OILS CYL','atlantic-marine-cylinder-oils-cyl','[{\"type\":\"heading\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Lubrication for the Cylinder Used in Two-Stroke Low-Speed Diesel Engines\"}],\"level\":2},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"ATLANTIC MARINE CYLINDER OILS are a wide variety of cylinder lubricants developed for use in all types of two-stroke low-speed diesel engines. These oils are available in a wide range of viscosities. They are designed to deliver outstanding performance in all operational settings, including full power, “slow,” and “flexible” steaming regimes, so that they may be used with engines that burn distillate as well as residual fuel. This makes them appropriate for use in a variety of applications.\"}]},{\"type\":\"heading\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"APPLICATIONS\"}],\"level\":2},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"ATLANTIC MARINE CYLINDER OILS were developed specifically for the purpose of lubricating the cylinders of all sorts of 2-stroke low-speed diesel engines that consume distillates and residual fuel oil with sulfur levels ranging from 0.5 to 3.5%.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"ATLANTIC MARINE CYL 25 is designed for low-speed engines that operate on ECA fuels with no more than 0.1% sulfur.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"ATLANTIC MARINE CYL 40 for engines operating at low speeds and burning low-sulfur fuel oil (LSFO).\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"ATLANTIC MARINE CYL 57 is designed for low-speed engines that operate on residual fuels containing between 0.5 and 3.5% percent sulfur.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"ATLANTIC MARINE CYL 70 for low-speed engines that operate on fuel oil with a high sulfur content (HSFO).\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"ATLANTIC MARINE CYL 100 is designed for newly developed low-speed engine designs that are susceptible to cold corrosion and that operate on high-sulfur fuel oil (HSFO).\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"ATLANTIC MARINE CYLINDER OILS were developed specifically for the new generation of highly rated, fuel-efficient, low-speed marine diesel engines that operate with greater pressures, higher temperatures, and longer strokes. This was done in order to specifically address all areas of oil stress.\"}]},{\"type\":\"heading\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"PRODUCT BENEFITS\"}],\"level\":2},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Very little wear on the piston rings and liners.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"The highest level of cleanliness.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Cost savings achieved in engine maintenance.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Helps prevent engine wear caused by deposits and scuffing, which are common problems with low-sulfur fuels.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"High resistance to heat and oxidation, which helps maintain performance throughout a wide range of engine operating circumstances.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Decreased amount of oil used in cylinders.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Long time between overhauls.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Developed with the detergent technology necessary to give an outstanding performance while using low-sulfur gasoline.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Strong control of piston groove deposits, which is a vital region for the functioning of distillate fuel, is provided by the detergency system.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Increased the amount of time between piston overhauls.\"}]},{\"type\":\"heading\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"RECOMMENDATIONS / SPECIFICATIONS\"}],\"level\":2},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"MAN Diesel & Turbo, MHI-MME and Wartsila, and Mitsubishi Heavy Industries are all considered to be met or exceeded.\"}]}]','2024-08-19 09:18:08.499000','2025-05-16 06:10:58.253000',NULL,2,2,'200,208,1000','OILS CYL',NULL,NULL,'ATLANTIC MARINE CYLINDER'),(32,'ATLANTIC SYNTHETIC HYDRAULIC OILS','atlantic-synthetic-hydraulic-oils','[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"ATLANTIC SYNTHETIC HYDRAULIC OILS are engineered to provide excellent wear protection for high-pressure vane, piston, and gear pumps in a wide range of temperatures. This helps to extend the life of machine components and makes ATLANTIC SYNTHETIC HYDRAULIC OILS ideal for use in a variety of applications. In addition to this, they contribute to the hydraulic system’s endurance, cleanliness, and efficiency.\"}]},{\"type\":\"heading\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"APPLICATIONS\"}],\"level\":2},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"ATLANTIC SYNTHETIC HYDRAULIC OILS are appropriate for the following applications:\",\"italic\":true}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Devices that typically have a very cold start-up temperature and extremely high operating temperatures.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Where it is impossible to avoid contact with trace amounts of water.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"In mechanical systems that consist of gears and bearings.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Hydraulic systems that are prone to deposit build-up, such as complex Numerically Controlled (NC) machines, particularly in situations where close clearance servo-valves are utilized.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Systems employing multi-metal component designs are also susceptible to deposit build-up.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Mobile hydraulic systems include those seen on dump trucks, motor graders, bulldozers, and forklifts, among other examples.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Three types of high-pressure pumps: vane, piston, and gear.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Those systems require a high degree of load-carrying capability and anti-wear protection.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Uses where the protection provided by a thin oil film against corrosion is advantageous, such as in systems that contain moisture.\"}]},{\"type\":\"heading\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"PROPERTIES\"}],\"level\":2},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"ATLANTIC SYNTHETIC HYDRAULIC OILS have exceptional performance at both low and high temperatures, which helps to provide an additional margin of equipment safety over and above what is possible with equivalent products based on mineral oil. The regulated demulsibility of the oils enables them to function properly in systems that are contaminated with trace amounts of water while at the same time easily separating significant quantities of water.\"}]},{\"type\":\"heading\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"PRODUCT BENEFITS\"}],\"level\":2},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Performance throughout a broad temperature range.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Superior protection against corrosion and oxidation; excellent oxidation stability.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Clean hydraulic systems.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Outstanding Resistance to Wear.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"High Value for the Viscosity Index.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Prevents the valve from becoming stuck.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Serves as a barrier against rust and corrosion.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Handles a Broad Variety of Equipment Needs.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Excellent compatibility with a variety of metals.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Outstanding Capabilities in the Area of Air Separation.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Demulsibility That Can Be Regulated.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Contributes to the reduction of system deposits and the risk of sludging.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Longer service life with reduced expenditures for equipment maintenance.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Reduces wear at temperatures below normal operating thresholds.\"}]},{\"type\":\"heading\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"RECOMMENDATIONS / SPECIFICATIONS\"}],\"level\":2},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"DENISON HF-0, HF-1, HF-2, VICKERS I-286-S, VICKERS M-2950-S , CINCINNATI MILACRON P-68, P-69, P-70\"}]}]','2024-08-19 09:57:11.775000','2025-04-14 09:57:21.697000',NULL,2,2,'5,20,25,208',NULL,NULL,NULL,'ATLANTIC SYNTHETIC HYDRAULIC OILS'),(33,'ATLANTIC SPINDLE – Spindle and Hydraulic Oils','atlantic-spindle-spindle-and-hydraulic-oils','[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"ATLANTIC SPINDLE OIL is made from a selection of high-quality, low-viscosity base oils and additives that provide excellent protection against oxidation as well as rust and corrosion.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"They have a high level of resistance to foaming and rapidly separate themselves from water. formulated solely for use in the lubricating of high-speed spindles found in many types of machine machines. Moreover, they are utilized in certain essential hydraulic circulation systems in addition to aviation oilers, provided that a suitable viscosity grade is chosen.\"}]},{\"type\":\"heading\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"PROPERTIES\"}],\"level\":2},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"As long as the appropriate viscosity is picked, ATLANTIC SPINDLE OIL possesses the required qualities to serve as low-pressure hydraulic and circulation oil. This is the case provided that the correct viscosity is selected. Because of this characteristic, inventory expenses can be kept to a minimum, and there is less chance that the product will be used incorrectly. ATLANTIC SPINDLE OIL provides superior lubrication of close-tolerance bearings, which helps keep the bearings operating cool and helps preserve the precision that is required by many of today’s important machine tools.\"}]},{\"type\":\"heading\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"PRODUCT FEATURES AND BENEFITS\"}],\"level\":2},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Lengthens the life of the equipment; Prevents moisture from entering regions of important lubrication.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Exhibits excellent Oxidation Resistance; Facilitates the Ease of Removing Moisture from System Reservoirs.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Prevents the production of emulsions.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Extremely effective protection against rust and corrosion.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Separation of water that is effective.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Helps to decrease the production of crucial deposits.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Long-term benefits include improved precision as well as extended oil life.\"}]},{\"type\":\"heading\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"APPLICATIONS\"}],\"level\":2},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"ATLANTIC SPINDLE OILS are formulated to be used in high-speed spindle bearings in machine tools and equipment where high speeds and fine clearances are involved; precision grinders, lathes, jig borers, and tracer mechanisms; as well as some sensitive instruments such as telescopes, laboratory equipment, etc.; and low pressure hydraulic systems where appropriate viscosity is selected. These lubricants are available in a wide range of viscosities. The relationship between clearance and spindle speed should be taken into consideration when selecting the appropriate viscosity for sleeve-type spindle bearings with larger clearances. ATLANTIC SPINDLE OIL ISO VG 2 is indicated for use in spindle bearings of the “zero clearance” type, which function with extremely near clearances.\"}]}]','2024-08-19 11:58:14.143000','2025-04-14 09:57:38.626000',NULL,2,2,'1,4,5,20,25,208','Spindle and Hydraulic Oils',NULL,NULL,'ATLANTIC SPINDLE'),(35,'ATLANTIC HYDRAULIC OILS HVI','atlantic-hydraulic-oils-hvi','[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"ATLANTIC HYDRAULIC OIL’s HVI\",\"bold\":true},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" series are high-performance, anti-wear hydraulic oils that have been designed expressly to fulfil the requirements of contemporary, high-pressure hydraulic systems found in industrial and mobile equipment. Maintaining optimal hydraulic efficiency and component safety at both low and high temperatures is made possible by the shear-stable, high viscosity index of the fluid. This allows the fluid to operate over a wide temperature range.\"}]},{\"type\":\"heading\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"APPLICATIONS\"}],\"level\":2},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"ATLANTIC HYDRAULIC OIL products of the HVI range come highly recommended for use in all types of hydraulic systems, including those that run at high temperatures and under high pressure (up to the limit specified by the pump manufacturer). Particularly well-suited for use in hydraulic systems that must function despite significant shifts in temperature as well as in machinery that must be operated in the open air: easy start-up at low temperatures; continuous operation throughout the year; civil engineering; machine tools; agriculture; marine; and transportation; and other industrial applications.\"}]},{\"type\":\"heading\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"PROPERTIES\"}],\"level\":2},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"ATLANTIC HYDRAULIC OIL HVI offers exceptional hydraulic system efficiency, exceptional performance in terms of keeping the fluid clean, and a high level of fluid durability. It is possible for the hydraulic efficiency feature to result in decreased energy consumption for both stationary and mobile equipment, which in turn can lower operating costs and boost overall productivity. Because of their superior oxidation and thermal stability, they can help to prolong the intervals between oil and filter changes, thereby contributing to the maintenance of clean systems. Their high level of anti-wear capabilities and outstanding film strength characteristics result in a high degree of equipment protection, which not only results in fewer breakdowns but also helps enhance production capacity. This is because fewer breakdowns mean less downtime for the equipment.\"}]},{\"type\":\"heading\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"PERFORMANCE FEATURES AND BENEFITS\"}],\"level\":2},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Very high value for the viscosity index.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Superior defense against the formation of rust and corrosion.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Excellent anti-foaming and air-release qualities are achieved by employing components without silicon.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"The extremely low point at which the liquid can be poured; good demulsibility, which ensures rapid water separation.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Outstanding filterability despite the presence of water in the environment.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"The high degree of operational dependability.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Sufficient shear stability.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Excellent thermal stability, preventing the production of sludge even when heated to high levels.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Extremely high resistance to oxidation ensures the fluid will have a long life in service. Strong resistance to wear, which ensures the longest possible life for the equipment.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Outstanding hydrolytic stability, which helps to prevent filter blockage.\"}]},{\"type\":\"heading\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"INDUSTRY SPECIFICATIONS\"}],\"level\":2},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"International Standards:\",\"bold\":true},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" AFNOR NF E 48-603 HV, ISO 6743/4 HV, DIN 51524 P3 HVLP, Swedish Standard (SS): 15 54 34 AM, ASTM: 6158-05 (HV fluids), GB: 111181-1-94 (HV fluids)\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Meets or Exceeds:\",\"bold\":true},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" VICKERS M-2950S, -I-286, DENISON HF0, HF1, HF2 (T6H20C), HUSKY HS 207, Cincinnati Machine: P-68 (ISO 32), P-70 (ISO 46), P-69 (ISO 68)\"}]}]','2024-08-20 06:21:47.315000','2025-04-14 09:57:49.591000',NULL,2,2,'5,20,25,208',NULL,NULL,NULL,'ATLANTIC HYDRAULIC OILS HVI'),(36,'ATLANTIC HYDRAULIC OILS FR','atlantic-hydraulic-oils-fr','[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"ATLANTIC HYDRAULIC OIL FR fluids are cutting-edge hydraulic fluids that are synthetic, anhydrous, and less flammable than conventional hydraulic fluids. They are formulated with organic esters and tried-and-true additives. They are engineered in a way that makes them superior to mineral oils when it comes to their resistance to catching fire, and they are designed to deliver excellent performance in conventional hydraulic systems. They are also capable of biodegradation and have a low eco-toxicity, making them an excellent choice for use in locations that are especially sensitive to the environment. ATLANTIC HYDRAULIC OIL FR reduces the risk of fire and damage to equipment, as well as the risk of disruptions and production stoppages. It also reduces the chance of injury to operators, which is a significant benefit.\"}]},{\"type\":\"heading\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"APPLICATIONS\",\"bold\":true}],\"level\":2},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"ATLANTIC HYDRAULIC OIL’s FR range comes highly recommended for use in settings where there is a risk of fire as well as in hydraulic fluid settings that are particularly conscious of their impact on the environment. The tunnel boring, metal, mining, and glass industries are excellent examples of typical applications of this technology. They can be used in hydraulic installations instead of mineral oils to offer the same level of good.\"}]},{\"type\":\"heading\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"PRODUCT BENEFITS\",\"bold\":true}],\"level\":2},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Reduced risk of ignition compared to mineral oils.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Readily biodegradable\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Low ecotoxicity, or the property of being “not damaging,” in the case of plants, invertebrates, and fish.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Very favorable viscosity and temperature properties.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Maintaining low flammability throughout the duration of the fluid’s use.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Good corrosion prevention.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Compatible with the vast majority of materials that have been specifically designated for use with mineral oils.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Protection against wear on the pump that is comparable to mineral hydraulic oils\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"RECOMMENDATIONS / SPECIFICATIONS\",\"bold\":true}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"ISO 6743/4 HFDU, ISO 12922, DIN 51502 HS-D\"}]}]','2024-08-20 06:48:35.960000','2025-04-14 09:58:03.399000',NULL,2,2,'5,20,25,208',NULL,NULL,NULL,'ATLANTIC HYDRAULIC OILS FR'),(37,'ATLANTIC HYDRAULIC OILS','atlantic-hydraulic-oils','[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"ATLANTIC HYDRAULIC OILS\",\"bold\":true},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" are premium performance, anti-wear hydraulic oils that have been developed to meet the needs of a diverse selection of hydraulic equipment specifications. They were designed to handle the critical requirements of other hydraulic system components such as close clearance servo-valves and the high accuracy numerically controlled (NC) machine tools. They were developed to meet the stringent requirements of severe hydraulic systems that use high-pressure, high-output pumps. In addition, they were designed to meet the stringent requirements of severe hydraulic systems. Designed to work with systems operating under severe conditions where high levels of antiwear and film strength protection are needed, yet they are formulated to work where non-antiwear hydraulic oils are generally recommended, these hydraulic fluids are made with high-quality base oils and a super-stabilized additive system that prevents the formation of corrosive materials. In addition, they are formulated to work with systems operating under severe conditions.\"}]},{\"type\":\"heading\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"APPLICATIONS\"}],\"level\":2},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"ATLANTIC HYDRAULIC OILS AW is formulated to offer superior protection in hydraulic vane-, piston-, and gear-type pumps found in mobile and stationary applications, as well as in high-performance industrial applications and locations that are very sensitive to the environment. Ideal for application in hydraulic systems of any kind, including those operating in the harshest environments, such as those found in machine tools, mold injection machines, presses, and other types of industrial or mobile equipment. Also utilized in many other applications, including those where a universal high-performance anti-wear lubricant is the first choice, such as air compressors, servo-motors, low-charged gears, sliding and rolling bearings, and control systems equipped with fine filtering systems.\"}]},{\"type\":\"heading\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"PROPERTIES\"}],\"level\":2},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Outstanding oxidation resistance is provided by ATLANTIC HYDRAULIC series products, which enables longer intervals between oil and filter changes. Their high level of anti-wear properties and excellent film strength characteristics result in exceptional equipment performance, which not only leads to fewer breakdowns but also helps improve production capacity. This is due to the fact that their high level of anti-wear properties and excellent film strength characteristics. The regulated demulsibility of the oils enables them to function properly in systems that are contaminated with trace amounts of water while at the same time easily separating significant quantities of water.\"}]},{\"type\":\"heading\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"PERFORMANCE FEATURES AND BENEFITS\"}],\"level\":2},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Excellent resistance to wear, ensuring the longest possible life for the equipment.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Excellent thermal stability, preventing the formation of sludge even when heated to very high. temperatures.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Excellent resistance to oxidation, guarantees a long life for the fluid in service.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Even under harsh service circumstances and during extended drain intervals, quality reserve ensures. performance characteristics are preserved.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Outstanding hydrolytic stability, which helps to prevent filter blockage.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Good protection against rust and corrosion.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Using components that are free of silicon allows for excellent anti-foam and air-release qualities.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Excellent demulsibility that allows for a speedy water separation.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Cost savings in both the maintenance and operating departments.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Outstanding filterability despite the presence of water in the environment.\"}]},{\"type\":\"heading\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"INDUSTRY SPECIFICATIONS\"}],\"level\":2},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"International Standards: AFNOR NF E 48-603 HM, ISO 6743/4 HM, DIN 51524 P2 HLP, CINCINNATI MILACRON P68, P69, P70\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Meets or Exceeds: VICKERS M-2950S, -I-286, DENISON HF0, HF1, HF2 (T6H20C), HUSKY HS 207\"}]}]','2024-08-20 07:08:06.852000','2025-04-14 09:58:17.251000',NULL,2,2,'5,20,25,208',NULL,NULL,NULL,'ATLANTIC HYDRAULIC OILS'),(38,'ATLANTIC SYNTHETIC DCT/DSG – Dual Wet Clutch Transmission Fluid','atlantic-synthetic-dct-dsg-dual-wet-clutch-transmission-fluid','[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"ATLANTIC SYNTHETIC DCT/DSG is a totally synthetic lubricant that was designed specifically for the dual-clutch transmissions (DCT) found in modern passenger automobiles. This lubricant combines carefully selected advanced DCT additive technology with high-quality base oils to create a unique formulation. It assures that these gears will operate without any issues and provides good friction stability in wet clutches.\"}]},{\"type\":\"heading\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"APPLICATIONS\"}],\"level\":2},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"ATLANTIC COMPLETELY SYNTHETIC DCT/DSG FLUID is an ideal choice for use as a service fill in the following applications:\",\"bold\":true}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Transmissions with six gears and a wet dual-clutch are available from Volkswagen, Seat, and Skoda (2003 to present).\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"6-speed wet Dual Clutch Transmissions are available from Ford, Volvo, Mitsubishi, PSA, and Chrysler (2007 to present).\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"BMW, Porsche & Mercedes-Benz, GETRAG’s Powershift 7DCL750 gearboxes, etc.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"This product is not designed to be used with Volkswagen dry clutch DSG types 0 AM, 02M, 02Q, or 02S.\"}]},{\"type\":\"heading\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"PROPERTIES\"}],\"level\":2},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"The ATLANTIC SYNTHETIC DCT/DSG is a transmission fluid of the highest quality that combines the capabilities of manual and automated transmissions. Because of its unique composition, it maintains consistent performance under a wide range of driving circumstances, including those that are particularly demanding. It makes a considerable contribution to the overall fuel efficiency.\"}]},{\"type\":\"heading\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"PRODUCT BENEFITS\"}],\"level\":2},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Protection against wear and a large extension of the transmission’s life.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Longer oil life because of exceptional resistance to heat and oxidation, exceptional shear stability. maximum fuel efficiency.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Improved friction durability for a more seamless performance from the transmission.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Good compatibility with the seal.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Excellent anti-shudder strength and durability.\"}]},{\"type\":\"heading\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"RECOMMENDATIONS / SPECIFICATIONS\"}],\"level\":2},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"BMW DCTF -1, MTF LT-5, CHRYSLER 68044345EA, FERRARI TF DCT -F3, FIAT 9.55550-MZ6, PSA 9734 S2, FORD WSS -M2C 936-A, WSS -M2C936-A, MB 236.21, 236.25, MITSUBISHI DIA MOND QUEEN SSTF -1, NISSAN R35 SPECIAL, PORSCHE 000.043.20, 000.043.207.29, 000.043.207.30, VOLVO BOT 341 #1161838, RENAULT BOT 450 EDC 6-Speed, VW G 052 182, G 052 529, G 052 513, TL 52182.\"}]}]','2024-08-20 07:40:58.138000','2025-03-25 06:25:42.156000',NULL,2,2,'1,4,208',NULL,NULL,NULL,'ATLANTIC SYNTHETIC DCT/DSG'),(39,'ATLANTIC ATF T4 – Automatic Transmission Fluid','atlantic-atf-t4-automatic-transmission-fluid','[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"ATLANTIC ATF T4 is a universal automatic transmission fluid (ATF) designed for the most recent generation of automatic transmissions. It is made from hydrocracking oils and PAO and contains specialized additives and inhibitors to ensure that the automatic transmission functions correctly.\"}]},{\"type\":\"heading\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"APPLICATIONS\"}],\"level\":2},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"ATLANTIC ATF T4 is an automatic transmission fluid that was designed specifically for use in Toyota and Aisin AW automatic transmissions.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"It is possible to use ATLANTIC ATF T4 in place of T, T-II, and T-III fluids.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Before adding fluid containing ATLANTIC ATF T4, it is recommended to first flush the system with ATLANTIC ATF T4.\"}]},{\"type\":\"heading\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"PRODUCT BENEFITS\"}],\"level\":2},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Provides the highest possible level of wear protection under any and all situations of operation.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Extremely good lubricating characteristics even while operating at low temperatures during the winter Protection against wear, corrosion, and foaming.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Behavior that is neutral with respect to the inhibition of non-ferrous metals.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Outstanding achievements both in terms of friction and anti-shudder.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Good viscosity stability while the machine is running Superb shift action with a pleasant feel.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"A viscosity index that is both high and steady.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Very low boiling point.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Very high resistance to oxidation.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Outstanding longevity as a result of the superior base oils and additives that it contains.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Behavior that is not biassed towards sealing materials.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Because it has such good oxidation resistance, the fluid has a long life.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Compatibility with materials made of synthetic rubber for sealing.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Opposition against the formation of foam.\"}]},{\"type\":\"heading\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"RECOMMENDATIONS / SPECIFICATIONS\"}],\"level\":2},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Fulfils the requirements for automatic transmission of Toyota and Aisin AW, Aisin Warner Automatic Gearbox, BMW 83 22 7 542 290 for MINI 6-Speed Aisin F21, 83 22 0 402 413 für MINI 6-Speed, Aisin F21 (nur USA), FORD 1327936, WSS-M2C924-A, XT-8QAW, General Motors 9986195, OPEL/GM 1940771, 1940774, Land Rover LR002748 6-Speed Aisin F21, RENAULT 7711218368 SU1 Gear, 7711172225 für Getriebe SU0 und SU1, TOYOTA JWS 3309, 08886-81016, 00279-000T4, 08886-01705, VOLVO 1161540, VW/AUDI G 055 025 A2, NISSAN 999MP-MTK00P für RE5F22A (Aisin AW55-50SN Nissan Altima, Maxima, Quest, Sentra), Matic K, Mazda K020-W0-049, b 99000-22800-001, ESSO JWS3317, Land Rover LR022460, Fiat 9.55550-AV1.\"}]}]','2024-08-20 08:15:53.979000','2025-04-09 07:23:10.118000',NULL,2,2,'1,4,208',NULL,NULL,NULL,'ATLANTIC ATF T4'),(40,'ATLANTIC ATF D6 – Fully Synthetic','atlantic-atf-d6-fully-synthetic','[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Atlantic ATF D6 is created using superior synthetic base stocks mixed with innovative additive technology. It satisfies all of the severe standards of General Motors’ DEXRON®-VI specification, which is designed for the contemporary automatic gearboxes found in GM automobiles. It is fully back-serviceable and can be utilized in places where DEXRON®-II and/or DEXRON®-III are advised. Atlantic ATF D6 is compatible with both modern and older GM automatic gearboxes, and it can be used in any one.\"}]},{\"type\":\"heading\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"PRODUCT BENEFITS\"}],\"level\":2},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Frictional qualities that have been optimized in order to offer smooth gear changing even when the temperature is low and to assist avoid transmission vibration.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Extends the life of the transmission fluid and stops the degradation of the fluid even at higher operating temperatures.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Enhanced resistance to oxidation and thermal stress.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Helps prevent the accumulation of varnish and sludge.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Performance that is exceptional even at low temperatures.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Helps to keep things lubricated.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Extensive testing in the field.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"When opposed to fluids manufactured to satisfy DEXRON®IIIH or previous requirements, low viscosity formulation offers advantages for fuel economy.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Enhanced anti-wear protection, which helps to contribute to a longer life for the transmission.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Protects the transmission gears and enables smooth operation of the gears themselves.\"}]},{\"type\":\"heading\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"APPLICATIONS\"}],\"level\":2},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Atlantic ATF D6 is a high-quality transmission fluid that can be utilized in wet clutches, power steering units, and automatic gearboxes with torque convertors found in passenger vehicles. Moreover, this transmission fluid can be utilized in power steering units.\"}]},{\"type\":\"heading\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"RECOMMENDATIONS / SPECIFICATIONS\"}],\"level\":2},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Meets or Exceeds General Motors DEXRON®-VI Requirements & for 2006 and newer GM vehicles.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Meets the performance requirements of MB 236.41, Allison C-4 & VOITH H55.6335xx.\"}]}]','2024-08-20 08:40:05.088000','2025-03-25 06:25:59.482000',NULL,2,2,'1,4,208',NULL,NULL,NULL,'ATLANTIC ATF D6'),(41,'ATLANTIC ATF D3 – Auto Transmission and Power Steering Fluid','atlantic-atf-d3-auto-transmission-and-power-steering-fluid','[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"ATLANTIC ATF DEXRONs are semi-synthetic lubricants designed for use in the majority of automatic transmissions. These lubricants have a very high viscosity index and are derived from carefully selected, highly refined base oils. The enhanced fluidity at low temperatures guarantees the best possible performance under any and all circumstances. Because of its remarkable frictional qualities, changing gears and driving are both made more comfortable.\"}]},{\"type\":\"heading\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"APPLICATIONS\"}],\"level\":2},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"ATLANTIC ATF DEXRON III is recommended for use in automatic transmissions, torque converters, power steering, and hydraulic circuits, for which the manufacturers prescribe a product, which meets the General Motors ATF TYPE Dexron III or Dexron II E and Ford Mercon requirements. These transmissions, torque converters, power steering, and hydraulic circuits are all examples of applications in which ATLANTIC ATF DEXRON III can be utilized (used in GM automatic transmissions pre-2005).\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Note that this should NOT be used in situations that require Dexron-VI, Mercon-V, Mercon-SP, or LV.\"}]},{\"type\":\"heading\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"PRODUCT BENEFITS\"}],\"level\":2},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Protection against wear and a large extension of the transmission’s life.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Longer oil life, superior stability against heat and oxidative breakdown.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"A larger capacity for both the clutch band and the clutch pack.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Ensuring that the power steering systems work effectively under all circumstances.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Improved friction durability for a more seamless performance from the transmission.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"A boost in the protection afforded to components made of copper and bronze.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Seal compatibility that works well cuts down on the possibility of leaks.\"}]}]','2024-08-20 09:08:39.907000','2025-03-25 06:26:15.220000',NULL,2,2,'1,4,208',NULL,NULL,NULL,'ATLANTIC ATF D3'),(42,'ATLANTIC TRANS HD','atlantic-trans-hd','[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"ATLANTIC TRANS HD Oils are intended to fulfill the exacting criteria demanded by Caterpillar TO-4, making them extremely high-performance transmission and drive-train lubricants. This product line features a distinctive design that was developed specifically to enhance the functionality of power shift transmissions, gearboxes, and final drives. They offer the highest level of protection possible, especially in high-pressure systems, when used in hydraulic applications. This technology combines a selection of base oils with an innovative additive system in order to give the precise performance parameters that are required to maximize the productivity of construction, quarrying, and mining equipment that is operating in harsh environments. When compared to the use of mixed fleet engine oils and lubricants that have been used in the past that satisfy Caterpillar TO-2 specifications, the performance of these products is demonstrably superior.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"The following transmissions are recommended for use with ATLANTIC TRANS HD Oils since they are the most demanding:\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Off-highway applications sometimes call for transmissions, gearboxes, final drives, and hydraulic systems that are designed for heavy loads.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Off-highway industries such as agriculture, mining, construction, and quarrying are included in this category.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Transmissions that require Allison C-4 fluids (specifically SAE 10W and 30 grades), such as manual, powershift, and automatic transmissions, as well as Twin Disc transmissions and transmissions that require Type F fluids.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Ideal for most mobile equipment hydraulic applications\"}]},{\"type\":\"heading\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"PROPERTIES\"}],\"level\":2},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"ATLANTIC TRANS HD is created to give exceptional oxidation stability, elastomer compatibility, control of corrosion and rust, and optimal protection against foaming. These benefits are all achieved through the formulation process. Both the grade SAE 10W’s low pour point and very good pumpability at low temperatures are hallmarks of this product.\"}]},{\"type\":\"heading\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"PRODUCT BENEFITS\"}],\"level\":2},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Slippage management and clutch-friction retention have both been optimized.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"A significant increase in the life of the clutch in comparison to the best API CD / Cat TO-2 engine oils.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Top performance in wet brakes, excellent   control of brake chatter.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Good pitting control.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Good foam control protection.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Excellent resistance to both heat and oxidation.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Greatly improved control of gear wear in transmissions, gearboxes and drive trains.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Superb FZG load-carrying capacity and FZG gear wear protection Very good low-temperature pumpability Good hydraulic oil stability and protection against high-pressure pump wear.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Great FZG load-carrying capability and FZG gear wear protection.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Friction coefficients, both static and dynamic, that are in good balance.\"}]},{\"type\":\"heading\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"RECOMMENDATIONS / SPECIFICATIONS\"}],\"level\":2},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Allison C-4, Caterpillar TO-4, ZF TE-ML-03, and Vickers 35 VQ 25 pump test are the models in question (HD 10W & HD 30)\"}]}]','2024-08-20 11:14:32.565000','2025-05-26 11:47:33.353000','2024-08-20 11:14:35.081000',2,4,'1,4,5,20,25,208','SAE 10W',NULL,NULL,'ATLANTIC TRANS HD'),(43,'ATLANTIC TOP GEAR OILS EP','atlantic-top-gear-oils-ep','[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"ATLANTIC TOP GEAR OILS EP is a series of premium mineral vehicle gear oil that is manufactured using current extreme pressure additives and friction modifiers. It satisfies the standards of API GL-5/6 and MT-1, in addition to the specifications of a great number of other manufacturers. When used in limited slip differentials, it eliminates the need for an additional product because it already contains the appropriate amount of restricted-slip additive in the precise dosage. Because of their mono-grade and multi-grade viscosity characteristics, they are able to fulfil the specifications set forth by a number of automobile manufacturers for the production of passenger cars as well as commercial trucks or buses.\"}]},{\"type\":\"heading\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"APPLICATIONS\"}],\"level\":2},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"ATLANTIC TOP GEAR OILS EP were developed specifically for use in hypoid and limited slip differentials, manual gearboxes, transfer cases, and transaxles in passenger cars, light commercial vehicles, four-wheel drive vehicles (4WDs), trucks, construction, earthmoving, and agricultural equipment. This viscosity grade is required in all of these types of equipment.\"}]},{\"type\":\"heading\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"PROPERTIES\"}],\"level\":2},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"ATLANTIC TOP GEAR OILS EP offers an exceptional level of protection in heavy-duty conditions, such as shock loads, hence minimising wear and extending the useful life of essential components. The formulation’s ability to serve several purposes enables greater flexibility while simultaneously reducing inventory levels, particularly for uses that are distinct from one another.\"}]},{\"type\":\"heading\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"PRODUCT BENEFITS\"}],\"level\":2},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Anti-shudder additive technique.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Exceptional consistency in temperature.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Longer drain intervals.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Compatible with any and all types of seals and metals.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Reduces the amount of stock held.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Large buffer zone for protection against foaming and corrosion.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Extraordinary defense against wear caused by scoring and spalling.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Helps to keep things clean while also cutting down on abrasive wear.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Very effective wear protection, even when subjected to extreme stress conditions.\"}]},{\"type\":\"heading\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"RECOMMENDATIONS / SPECIFICATIONS\"}],\"level\":2},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"API GL-5/GL-6/MT-1/PG-2, MIL-L-2105D, L-PRF-2105E, GM HN 1181/1187/1386/1561, China National GB 13895-1992, Ford ESW-M2C1006-B/1013-A/104-A/105-A/197-A Meets or exceeds the quality requirements of numerous vehicle manufacturers such as IVECO, MAN, SCANIA and VOLVO for heavy vehicles rear axles and final drive units.\"}]}]','2024-08-21 05:41:27.040000','2025-05-26 11:44:22.527000','2024-08-21 05:41:30.593000',2,4,'1,4,5,20,25,200,208',NULL,'API GL-5',NULL,'ATLANTIC TOP GEAR OILS EP'),(44,'ATLANTIC SYNTHETIC GEAR OIL','atlantic-synthetic-gear-oil','[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"ATLANTIC Synthetic Gear oil 75W-85 is a smooth-shifting, extreme-pressure API GL-4 totally synthetic gear oil that outperforms conventional mineral gear oils in terms of its stability at high temperatures. It was developed by ATLANTIC. Perfect for usage in applications involving transaxles that have manual gearboxes and differentials merged into one unit. It is made with hydro-finished base fluids and excellent additive packages to boost wear protection, corrosion protection, seal compatibility, and low-temperature characteristics. The formulation is done utilising hydro-finished base fluids.\"}]},{\"type\":\"heading\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"APPLICATIONS\"}],\"level\":2},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"In situations where API GL-4 is required, transaxles with a combined manual gearbox and hypoid differential are available.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Automobiles for passengers, vehicles capable of towing, four-wheel drive, and light commercial vehicles.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Spiral bevel gears and hypoid gears, both of which are working under conditions of moderate speed and weight.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Some manual transmissions and transaxles, for which API MT-1 is not an appropriate specification.\"}]},{\"type\":\"heading\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"PRODUCT FEATURES & BENEFITS\"}],\"level\":2},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Reduces the likelihood of the shifter sticking when it’s cold.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"For a longer component life, having good corrosion protection and rust avoidance is essential.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"The feel of shifting is consistent for the duration of the oil’s life.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"lowering the number of hazardous deposits.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Will not be harmful to bronze or brass.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Includes synthetic base oils, which contribute to longer product life.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Very high oil film strength, affording superior protection.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Performance that is superior even when the temperature is low High viscosity index for performance that is superior even when the temperature is high in operation.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Outstanding performance in terms of wear reduction and friction behavior.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Superior resistance to heat and oxidation, resulting in a longer service life.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"able to work with various synchro materials.\"}]},{\"type\":\"heading\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"RECOMMENDATIONS / SPECIFICATIONS\"}],\"level\":2},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"API GL-4 Plus, GM 12346190, MB 235.10/235.4, Chrysler MS 9224, ZF TE-ML 01/02/08, BTR 5M42, MAN 341, US Military MIL-L-2105, Ford ESW-M2C-83A/B, ESPM2C-83, WSD M2C200-C, GM HN 1046, 1070, 1820, 1855, 2276.\"}]}]','2024-08-21 05:55:17.355000','2025-05-26 11:44:48.716000','2024-08-21 05:55:25.199000',2,4,'1,4,5,20,25,200,208','SAE 75W 85','API GL-4',NULL,'ATLANTIC SYNTHETIC GEAR OIL'),(45,'ATLANTIC SYN TRANS MV','atlantic-syn-trans-mv','[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"ATLANTIC SYN TRANS MV\",\"bold\":true},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" Oils are entirely synthetic drivetrain lubricants that were designed to fulfill the most stringent extended drain and OEM warranty standards. These lubricants are also environmentally friendly. These products are intended for use in heavy-duty drivetrains, which call for gear lubricants to have good load-carrying capacity. These drivetrains also operate in environments that are subject to intense pressures and shock loads. The cutting-edge technology provides unrivaled performance for applications operating at low and high temperatures, including exceptional oxidation stability, wear protection, corrosion resistance, increased shear stability, prolonged service capability, and good fuel economy.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"APPLICATIONS ATLANTIC SYN TRANS MV\",\"bold\":true},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" Oils are synthetic-based oils that are developed for the lubrication of all gearboxes and axles that require an API GL-5 level and a viscosity of SAE 75W-90 / 80W-140. These oils are available in two different viscosities: 75W-90 and 80W-140.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Heavy-duty manual transmissions, axles, and final drives must meet the performance standards of API GL-5 and MT-1.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Trucks of light and large loads, buses, and vans operating on the highway\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Off-highway industries such as agriculture, construction, mining, and quarrying are included in this category.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Other types of heavy-duty industrial gear drives, such as hypoid and worm gears, may be required to operate in environments characterized by high speed and shock load, high speed and\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"low torque, or low speed and high torque, respectively.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Equipment that operates in extremely low temperatures, such as winch reduction gears and crawler vehicle propulsion gear drives, should use this product.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Not recommended for use in applications that require performance at the API GL-4 level.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Not designed for automatic, manual, or semiautomatic transmissions engine oil or fluids designed for automatic transmissions are advised for those types of transmissions.\"}]},{\"type\":\"heading\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"PRODUCT FEATURES & BENEFITS\"}],\"level\":2},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Superb performance from the synchronizer, resulting in increased synchronizer life as well as shift comfort.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Extraordinary cold flow capabilities that allow for a more seamless gear shift when temperatures are low.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Capability for high loads and high torques throughout a wide variety of application fields.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"High Extreme-Pressure characteristics.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Outstanding consistency throughout the service.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Fluid multigrade oil based on synthetic components.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Outstanding hydraulic oil stability and protection against wear on the high-pressure pump.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Advantages of having a low viscosity when the temperature is low.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Protects the moving parts and enhances the vehicle’s drivability.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Outstanding wear resistance, together with strong oxidation and corrosion resistance, and anti-rust qualities.\"}]},{\"type\":\"heading\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"RECOMMENDATIONS / SPECIFICATIONS\"}],\"level\":2},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"API GL-5/MT-1, BTR 5M-50, MIL-L-2105D, ZF TE ML-01/02/05/07/08, Scania STO 1:0, SAE J2360, MB 235.8, MAN 342 Typ M2, Voith Turbo 132.00374401/132.00374402.\"}]}]','2024-08-21 07:19:59.840000','2025-05-26 11:45:09.495000','2024-08-21 07:20:03.729000',2,4,'1,4,5,20,25,200,208','SAE 75W 90','API GL-5',NULL,'ATLANTIC SYN TRANS MV'),(46,'ATLANTIC GEAR OILS LS','atlantic-gear-oils-ls','[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"ATLANTIC GEAR OILS LS are outstanding sulfur-phosphorus, severe pressure gear lubricants that are made with premium quality base stocks to satisfy the criteria for excellent performance. These lubricants are designed for use in environments that experience high levels of pressure. This oil has the requisite properties to be used in differentials, and those differentials are equipped with a “limited-slip” mechanism. These features are imparted to the oil via a particular friction additive. 4\"}]},{\"type\":\"heading\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"APPLICATIONS\"}],\"level\":2},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"ATLANTIC GEAR OILS LS are generally suggested for use in conventional rear axles, restricted slip rear axles, and gearboxes that call for EP gear lubes in conditions characterised by high speed, high load, high torque, and high horsepower. Because this product already contains a Limited Slip Friction Modifier, it eliminates the need for most vehicles to have an extra friction modifier installed.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"ATLANTIC GEAR OILS LS has increased frictional qualities and is designed for use in applications with limited slip. This transmission oil is of the highest quality, and it is packed with superior additives and carefully chosen base oils. As a result, it offers great protection against oxidation, corrosion, and rust, and it also helps increase gear life.\"}]},{\"type\":\"heading\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"PRODUCT BENEFITS\"}],\"level\":2},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Superior ability to support a loaded burden\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Extreme pressure properties\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Large buffer zone for protection against foaming and corrosion\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Exceptional consistency in temperature\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"The capability of service-filling limited slips\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Longer drain intervals\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Addition of stable amounts of sulfur and phosphorus\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Demulsibility\"}]},{\"type\":\"heading\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"RECOMMENDATIONS / SPECIFICATIONS\"}],\"level\":2},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"API GL-5, MIL MIL -L-2105 C, MIL MIL -L-2105 D, ZF TE-ML 05 Meets or exceeds the quality requirements of numerous vehicle manufacturers such as IVECO, MAN, SCANIA and VOLVO for heavy vehicles rear axles and final drive units.\"}]}]','2024-08-21 08:09:33.822000','2025-05-26 11:46:24.031000','2024-08-21 08:09:37.251000',2,4,'1,4,5,20,25,200,208','SAE 80W 90','API GL-5',NULL,'ATLANTIC GEAR OILS LS'),(47,'ATLANTIC GEAR OILS HYPOID','atlantic-gear-oils-hypoid','[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"ATLANTIC GEAR OILS HP\",\"bold\":true},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" is part of a more modern range of products that are designed to be particularly suited to the most rigorous service conditions that can be found in automotive mechanical transmission (light and heavy-duty vehicles), agricultural machinery, civil engineering, and handling equipment. They are engineered to work exclusively with the hypoid gear axles and mechanical gearboxes found in automobiles and commercial trucks. It is designed for all high-performance hypoid axles of cars, pickup trucks, and sports utility vehicles, as well as racing cars, sports cars, and police cars. It can be used as a makeup or refill of the fluid, even for repaired limited slip units. It is also compatible with rebuilt limited slip units. Moreover, it is suggested for use with traditional differentials.\"}]},{\"type\":\"heading\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"PRODUCT FEATURES & BENEFITS\"}],\"level\":2},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Excellent performance under tremendous pressure, including anti-wear, anti-scuffing, and anti-foaming qualities.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Strong resistance to deterioration, guarantees consistent performance even when working in environments where temperatures are elevated.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Extended life of the transmission.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Outstanding synchronizer performance, resulting in a longer synchronizer life and improved shift comfort.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Having no effect on seals, even when exposed to high temperatures.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Abilities to prevent rusting and corrosion, protecting steel and copper from the damaging effects of contact with water.\"}]},{\"type\":\"heading\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"RECOMMENDATIONS / SPECIFICATIONS\"}],\"level\":2},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"API GL-5\"}]}]','2024-08-21 08:42:02.324000','2025-05-26 11:45:47.101000','2024-08-21 08:42:07.143000',2,4,'1,4,5,20,25,200,208','SAE 85W 140','API GL-5',NULL,'ATLANTIC GEAR OILS'),(48,'ATLANTIC GEAR OILS HD PLUS','atlantic-gear-oils-hd-plus','[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"ATLANTIC GEAR OILS HD PLUS Oils\",\"bold\":true},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" are extra high-performance commercial gear lubricants that are created from select base oils and an innovative additive system. These oils were developed by ATLANTIC GEAR OILS. The performance of these lubricants has been optimized for use in heavy-duty commercial transmissions, axles, and final drives. They offer a very high level of protection under all conditions, including strong shock loads, thereby preventing wear and extending the life of essential components. They exhibit great chemical and thermal stability at elevated bulk oil temperatures, acceptable performance at low temperatures, and have exhibited outstanding protection against rust that is caused by water contamination and moist environments.\"}]},{\"type\":\"heading\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"APPLICATIONS\"}],\"level\":2},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"ATLANTIC GEAR OILS HD PLUS The following are some of the applications that are designed to benefit from the lubrication provided by oils:\",\"italic\":true}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Transmissions, axles, and final drives for heavy-duty vehicles must meet the performance standards of API GL-5 and MT-1.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Trucks, both light and heavy-duty, buses, vans, and cars that are driven on the highway\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Off-highway industries such as agriculture, construction, mining, and quarrying are included in this category.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Additional heavy-duty industrial and automotive applications involving hypoid and other gears that must operate under conditions that include high speed and shock load, high speed and low torque, and/or low speed and high torque.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Initial filling, topping off, and subsequent refilling of enclosed commercial gearing in manual or semiautomatic transmissions where gear lubricants are suggested; this includes drive axles and final drives.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Not recommended for use in applications that require performance at the API GL-4 level.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Not suitable for transmissions that require engine oil or automatic transmission fluids; these products should not be used in those applications.\"}]},{\"type\":\"heading\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"PRODUCT FEATURES & BENEFITS\"}],\"level\":2},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"High resistance to oxidation at high temperatures as well as excellent thermal stability.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Excellent protection against wear at low speed and high torque as well as against scoring at high speed.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Extended drain periods are achieved by being resistant to high-temperature deterioration.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Compatible with the standard seals and gaskets used in automobiles.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Protection against rust, corrosion, and stains of the highest quality.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Lubrication that is efficient even at low temperatures.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Excellent resistance to foaming.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Added technology that provides maximum protection from trembling.\"}]},{\"type\":\"heading\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"RECOMMENDATIONS / SPECIFICATIONS\"}],\"level\":2},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"API GL-5/MT-1, Scania STO 1:0, SAE J2360, Mack GO-J, MIL-PRF-2105E, L-2105D, GM HN 1181/1386, Chrysler MS-9020, Rockwell O-76A, Clark MS-8, White MS-0016, ZF TE-L05A/05C/07A/08/12C/16/21, Mack GO-J, International B-22, Ford ESW-M2C105-A/197-A, BTR 5M-36.\"}]}]','2024-08-21 09:00:17.385000','2025-05-26 11:45:27.339000','2024-08-21 09:00:21.980000',2,4,'1,4,5,20,25,200,208','SAE J23 60','API GL-5/MT-1',NULL,'ATLANTIC GEAR OILS'),(49,'ATLANTIC CVT FLUID – Multi-Vehicle Synthetic Fluid','atlantic-cvt-fluid-multi-vehicle-synthetic-fluid','[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"ATLANTIC SYNTHETIC MULTI-VEHICLE CVT FLUID is a fully synthetic lubricant that has been intended to be used in the majority of CVT gears. It is based on base oils that have been extremely carefully selected for their very high quality. It is appropriate for continuously variable transmissions that employ chains or steel push belts as the transmission medium. It provides exceptional protection against wear and has friction characteristics that are consistent.\"}]},{\"type\":\"heading\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"PROPERTIES\"}],\"level\":2},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"ATLANTIC SYNTHETIC MULTI-VEHICLE CVT FLUID offers superior metal-to-metal frictional qualities as well as good protection and performance for CVTs throughout the drain intervals that are advised by the vehicle manufacturer. It is Warranty Secure, which means that it will not violate the warranty on your vehicle. A cost-effective and high-performance alternative to the fluids provided by the original equipment manufacturer (OEM), ATLANTICSYNTHETIC MULTI-VEHICLE CVT FLUID is a synthetic fluid that may be used in several vehicles.\"}]},{\"type\":\"heading\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"PRODUCT BENEFITS\"}],\"level\":2},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"High resistance to wear and friction high heat tolerance excellent frictional characteristics.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"The exceptional performance of the wet clutch helps avoid slippage of the belt and chain and increases the life of the transmission.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Protects the important components of the transmission from wear in an efficient manner, hence extending their lifespan.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"The exceptional performance of the wet clutch, resulting in remarkable anti-shudder longevity.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Superior resistance to heat and oxidation; prolonged service life for the oil.\"}]},{\"type\":\"heading\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"APPLICATIONS\"}],\"level\":2},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"ATLANTIC SYNTHETIC MULTI-VEHICLE CVT FLUID is formulated by carefully balancing different base oils and modern additives in order to suit the standards of CVT producers in both Europe and Japan. It is possible that some hybrid vehicles, which need specific fluids, cannot use this product since it is not compatible.\"}]},{\"type\":\"heading\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"RECOMMENDATIONS / SPECIFICATIONS\"}],\"level\":2},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"AUDI TL 52180, DAIHATSU AMIX CVTF DFE, CVTF-DC, FORD WSS -M2C928-A, CVT23, CVT30, MERCON C, GM SATURN DEX-CVT, HONDA HCF -2, HMMF, HYUNDAI SP -CVT1, SP –III, KIA SP –III, MB 236.20, MINI EZL799A, MITSUBISHI CVTF -J1/SP –III, CVTF J-4, NISSAN NS-1/NS-2/NS-3, SUBARU CVT, Lineartronic CVTF, i-CVT, SUZUKI CVTF GREEN 2, TC /NS -2/CVT Green 1, TOYOTA TC, CVT FE, VW G 052 180, G 052 516, BMW 8322 0 136 376, 8322 0 429 154, DODGE/JEEP NS-2, CVTF+4®, MOPAR® CVT 4, ZF CVT V1.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Meets or exceeds the quality requirements of most American, Japanese and European manufacturers.\",\"italic\":true}]}]','2024-08-21 10:07:29.018000','2025-03-25 06:26:35.605000',NULL,2,2,'1,4,208',NULL,NULL,NULL,'ATLANTIC CVT FLUID'),(50,'Atlantic Zero Zero Sodium Grease','atlantic-zero-zero-sodium-grease','[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Proven performance fibrous Sodium Soap Greases. Their fibrous content offers protection from contaminants such as dust and dirt by helping provide a reliable seal.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"ATLANTIC –Zero Zero Sodium Greases have a sodium component, designed to provide inherent rust protection capability, by emulsifying small amounts of water.\"}]},{\"type\":\"heading\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Customer benefits\"}],\"level\":2},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Offers reliable film strength\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Good surface adhesion\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Promotes dirt and dust protection\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Designed for inherent rust protection\"}]},{\"type\":\"heading\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Recommendations\"}],\"level\":2},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"ATLANTIC –Zero Zero Sodium Greases are recommended for use as chassis lubricants for passenger cars, trucks, buses, farm and construction equipment\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"It is also recommended for centralized lubrication systems\"}]}]','2024-08-21 10:30:54.119000','2024-08-31 06:28:16.238000','2024-08-22 05:28:39.124000',2,2,NULL,'Sodium Grease',NULL,NULL,'Atlantic Zero Zero'),(51,'Atlantic CALCIUM GREASE MP','atlantic-calcium-grease-mp','[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"ATLANTIC CALCIUM GREASE MP is calcium –based grease specially formulated for vehicle chassis lubrication and protection. It is water resistant and contains extreme pressure and tackiness agents, making it particularly effective in severe application such as large trucks and off-highway equipment, used in the construction industry. It is available NLGI NO. 2&3 grade and pump able from centralized greasing systems even at low temperature\"}]},{\"type\":\"heading\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Features and Benefits\"}],\"level\":2},{\"type\":\"list\",\"format\":\"unordered\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"list-item\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Long service life\"}]},{\"type\":\"list-item\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Excellent Tackiness\"}]},{\"type\":\"list-item\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Good pump ability\"}]},{\"type\":\"list-item\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Good water resistance\"}]},{\"type\":\"list-item\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Good shear – stability and resistance to vibration\"}]}]}]','2024-08-22 05:35:55.482000','2025-05-26 11:58:55.927000','2024-08-22 05:35:58.729000',2,4,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Atlantic CALCIUM GREASE MP'),(52,'Atlantic Lithium Wheel Bearing Grease MP3','atlantic-lithium-wheel-bearing-grease-mp-3','[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Atlantic Lithium Wheel Bearing Grease MP3 is Lithium MP Grease made from high quality mineral oil thickened with lithium soap and fortified with functional additives to impart oxidation and corrosion resistance.\"}]},{\"type\":\"heading\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Applications\"}],\"level\":2},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Atlantic Lithium Wheel Bearing Grease MP3 is recommended for multipurpose applications including high performance wheel bearing, chassis points, and water pump bearing. They are pumpable and can be dispensed by and greasing system. MP 3 Grease is recommended for all normal grease application areas.\"}]}]','2024-08-22 05:44:17.710000','2025-05-26 12:26:05.161000','2024-08-22 05:44:21.401000',2,4,NULL,'Wheel Bearing Grease MP3',NULL,NULL,'Atlantic Lithium'),(53,'Atlantic Chassis Grease','atlantic-chassis-grease','[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"ATLANTIC CHASSIS GREASE is Calcium –based grease specially formulated for vehicle chassis lubrication and protection. It is water resistant and contains extreme pressure and tackiness agents, making it particularly effective in severe application such as large trucks and off-highway equipment used in the construction industry. It is an NLGI NO 1 grade and pumpable from centralized greasing systems even at low temperatures.\"}]},{\"type\":\"heading\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"PRODUCT BENEFITS\"}],\"level\":2},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Long service life\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Good shear –stability and resistance to vibration\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Excellent Tackiness\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Good pumpability\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Good water resistance\"}]}]','2024-08-22 05:53:14.920000','2024-08-31 06:36:23.701000','2024-08-22 05:53:17.306000',2,2,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Atlantic Chassis Grease'),(54,'ATLANTIC WHEEL BEARING GREASE – Sodium Base Grease','atlantic-wheel-bearing-grease-sodium-based','[{\"type\":\"heading\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"DESCRIPTION & APPLICATIONS\"}],\"level\":2},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"ATLANTIC WHEEL BEARING GREASE is a high quality, sodium base grease specially developed for lubrication of automotive wheel bearings over a wide range of temperature with excellent high temperature performance. These are ideally suited for application by centralized grease systems due to good resistance to oil separation under pressure mechanical stability.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"ATLANTI