tifreeze that has a combination of organic additive technology inhibitors as well as borate, nitrite, nitrate, molybdate, and silicate inorganic corrosion inhibitors. These inhibitors work together to prevent freezing in a variety of environments. It is an antifreeze that contains no phosphates or amines, has a low silicate content, and is suited for use in heavy-duty applications without the need for additional coolant additives.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Dose Rate – Mix Ratio        33% 50%               Freezing Point        -18°C -38°C                  Boiling Point        +104°C +109°C\"}]},{\"type\":\"heading\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"PRODUCT FEATURES AND BENEFITS\"}],\"level\":2},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Prevents corrosion on all internal surfaces, including aluminum, and other materials.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Long-lasting coolant and inhibitor combination pack.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"The formulation that does not contain phosphate.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Prepared for use and requires no mixing.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Efficient cooling of the engine that does not cause boiling.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"A cooling system that is free of debris and provides defense against buildups of scale and sludge.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Compatible with all different kinds of coolant.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Will not discolor original coolant.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Conversable avec les plastiques, les caoutchoucs, et les scelle.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Lubrication of water pumps that is both effective and efficient.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"compatibility with many types of rubber.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"a measure of defense against the cold.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Precautions to be taken to avoid electrolysis.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Protection against the corrosion caused by cavitation.\"}]},{\"type\":\"heading\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"APPLICATIONS\"}],\"level\":2},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"ATLANTIC RADIATOR COOLANT can be used in the radiator cooling systems of all types of passenger vehicles, 4WDs, light and heavy-duty commercial vehicles, motorcycles, and stationary engines. Both Organic Acid Technology (OAT) and Hybrid Type A anti-freeze/anti-boil coolants, in addition to Type B inhibitor alone solutions, can benefit from its use as a topping-off agent. It is completely risk-free to use wherever anti-freeze, anti-boil, and anti-corrosion capabilities are required, as well as with all types of fuel, including gasoline, liquid petroleum gas (LPG), dual fuel, and light and heavy-duty diesel. Because it has already been diluted to a concentration of 50% with demineralized water, the product is ready to use as soon as it is removed from the bottle.\"}]},{\"type\":\"heading\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"FILLING INSTRUCTION:\"}],\"level\":2},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Wait until the cooling system has fully cooled down before continuing.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Take off the cap of the radiator or the cap of the overflow reservoir.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Put the substance straight to the cooling system through the radiator or the overflow reservoir.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Replace the cap on the radiator or the reservoir safely.\"}]},{\"type\":\"heading\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"RECOMMENDATIONS / SPECIFICATIONS\"}],\"level\":2},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"AS2108-2004 Type A, ASTM D3306/4985, BS 6580, JIS K 2234-97, Class 2, Jaguar M97-B44D, Bentley, Caterpillar EC-1, Cummins 85T8-2/CESMG03, Chrysler MS-9769, Deutz AG 0199-99-1115/2091, Federal Standard O-A-548D, Fiat 955523/NC 956-16, Ford M97-B44A/B44D/51A, German Army TL6850-0038/1, GM 6277M/1825M/1899M, Holden HN2217/HN2043, Jenbacher TA 1000-0201, JI Case JIC 501, JIS K2234 (Japan), JCB STD 0088, JASO M325 (Japan), John Deere JDM H24, Komatsu KES 07.892, KSM 2142 (Korea), TMC RP329,Leyland BLS.22.AF.01, Liebherr MD 1-36-130, Mack 014 GS 17009, Mercedes MB 325.3/326.0/326.3 (Premix Only), Navistar B1 Type III, Mitsubishi ES-X64217, MTU MTL 5048, Renault 41-01-001Q Type D, Nissan NES M5059, Opel B 040 1065, QL 13D100, SAE J1034, Rover BLS.22.AF.01, SAAB GM6277, Scania T1.02-98 0813, UNE 26.361.88, Toyota Long Life TSK2601G, Vauxhall B 040 1065, Volvo VCS, VW, Skoda, Seat TL-774-C (G11), VW, Audi, Skoda, Seat, Lamborghini TL 774-D/F (G12/G12+).\"}]}]','2024-08-23 10:10:39.203000','2024-08-31 07:15:11.398000','2024-08-23 10:10:44.827000',2,2,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'ATLANTIC RADIATOR COOLANT'),(72,'ATLANTIC ANTIFREEZE – Concentrated','atlantic-antifreeze-concentrated','[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"ATLANTIC ANTIFREEZE is an ethylene glycol antifreeze that is heavy-duty, long-lasting, undiluted, and completely prepared. It also contains anti-corrosion inhibitors. It provides protection that is both comprehensive and ongoing for the cooling system. It does not have any nitrates, phosphates, or amines in its composition.\"}]},{\"type\":\"heading\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"APPLICATIONS\"}],\"level\":2},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"ATLANTIC ANTIFREEZE was formulated for application in open or closed cooling circuits, depending on the application (vehicles and heating). Appropriate for use in automobiles as well as heavy-duty gasoline and diesel engines, such as those found in on-road, off-road, marine, agricultural, mining, and construction equipment. Dilute with water that has had its minerals removed.\"}]},{\"type\":\"heading\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"PROPERTIES\"}],\"level\":2},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"ATLANTIC ANTIFREEZE is a hybrid antifreeze that has a combination of organic additive technology inhibitors together with borate, nitrite, nitrate, molybdate, and silicate inorganic corrosion inhibitors. These inhibitors work together to protect against corrosion and prevent freezing. It is an antifreeze that contains no phosphates or amines, has a low silicate content, and is suited for use in heavy-duty applications without the need for additional coolant additives.\"}]},{\"type\":\"heading\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"PRODUCT BENEFITS\"}],\"level\":2},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Anti-corrosion inhibitors; protects against freezing temperatures down to -37 degrees Celsius and boilover temperatures up to 129 degrees Celsius.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Free of both amines and phosphates.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"A cooling system that is free of debris and provides defense against buildups of scale and sludge.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Service is typically guaranteed for a period of five years or 240,000 kilometers.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Compatible with different types of engine antifreeze and able to dissolve in them.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"A low silicate level also ensures that the material is compatible with aluminum.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"A measure of defense against the cold.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Prevention against the corrosion caused by cavitation.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Efficient cooling of the engine that prevents overheating.\"}]},{\"type\":\"heading\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"FILLING INSTRUCTION\"}],\"level\":2},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Diluted with clean water (preferably de-mineralized water) to a concentration between 30 and 50 percent, which is the recommended concentration to achieve the highest degree of protection performance for larger diesel engines. At a concentration of 30 percent, the anti-corrosion treatment provides a satisfactory level of protection against corrosion for light vehicles. ATLANTIC ANTIFREEZE will give optimal performance and protection in a clean cooling system for up to one year, at which point the system should be drained and refilled before continuing to be used. Antifreeze that has been diluted with the right amount of water should be used when topping off the system.\"}]},{\"type\":\"heading\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"RECOMMENDATIONS / SPECIFICATIONS\"}],\"level\":2},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"ASTM D3306,D4985, D6210 AFNOR 15-601/1991, BS 6580-1992, SAE: J1034, US Fed: A-A-870-A. AS/NZ: 2108.1:1997 ‘Type A’, Caterpillar: EC-1 (sections 2.3–4.5 included), Cummins: Bulletin 3666132, JLS: K 2234, Volvo, Daimler Chrysler: MS 9769, Detroit Diesel: 7SE298; 93K217, Freightliner: 48-22880, General Motors: 1825M, 1899M, Heavy Truck, John Deere: JDM H24, Kenworth: RO26-170-97, MACK Truck: 014GS17004, MAN: 324, Merecedes-Benz: DBL 7700, MTU: MTL 5048, PACCAR: CSO185, Scania: TB1451, TMC: RP 329, Daimler Chrysler: MS 7170, Ford: ESE-M97B44-A, Scania: 6901, ESE-M97B18-C, John Deere: HD 24, International (IT&E): CEMS B-1, New Holland: WSN-M97B18-D, Peterbilt: 8502.002.\"}]}]','2024-08-23 12:08:24.344000','2024-09-05 08:21:25.379000','2024-08-23 12:08:28.663000',2,3,'1,4,5,208',NULL,NULL,NULL,'ATLANTIC ANTIFREEZE – Concentrated'),(73,'ATLANTIC FRENO BRAKE FLUID DOT 4','atlantic-freno-brake-fluid-dot-4','[{\"type\":\"heading\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"DESCRIPTION\"}],\"level\":2},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"ATLANTIC FRENO BRAKE FLUID DOT 4 is premium quality, non-silicone, non-mineral/petroleum based, fully synthetic brake fluid designed for use in a wide range of brake and clutch applications. It offers superior dry and wet boiling points and maintains viscosity in cold and hot environments.\"}]},{\"type\":\"heading\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"APPLICATIONS\"}],\"level\":2},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Recommended for re-fill or top-up of brake and clutch systems in passenger cars, 4WD\'s, motorcycles, light and heavy duty commercial vehicles, mining, construction and agricultural equipment that require a non-petroleum based brake & clutch hydraulic fluid. ATLANTIC FRENO BRAKE FLUID DOT 4 is suitable for use where the vehicle manufacturer specifies DOT 3 or DOT 4 brake fluid. Better performance for life of fluid compared to DOT 3 fluids.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"text\":\"NOTE:\",\"type\":\"text\",\"bold\":true},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" Intermixing of brake fluids of different grades is not recommended. Intermixing may\\r impact braking performance of some brake systems. This product is not miscible with silicone\\r based brakefluids. This product is not compatible with any mineral or synth