 properties.\"}]}]},{\"type\":\"list\",\"format\":\"unordered\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"list-item\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Extend the life of engine.\"}]}]},{\"type\":\"list\",\"format\":\"unordered\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"list-item\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Longer Oil Life.\"}]}]},{\"type\":\"heading\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Recommendations/Specifications\"}],\"level\":2},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"ATLANTIC MARINOL S meets or exceeds the quality requirements of MTU Type II, Wärtsilä, MWM Deutz, Caterpillar 3600 Series.                                                    \"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"API service: CH-4, CF, ACEA E7\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"ATLANTIC MARINOL W meets or exceeds the quality requirements of CUMMINS CES 200-71,-72, 76, (B&C Series) CES 200-75, Mitsubishi, Perkins, Caterpillar: ECF-2, MTU MTL 5044 Category 1 / 2, Mercedes Benz 228.3, MAN 3275, Volvo VDS 2, GM Allison C-4\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"API service: CI-4, CH-4,  ACEA: E3, E5, A2, B3.\"}]}]','2025-05-16 07:28:48.974000','2025-05-16 07:28:50.918000','2025-05-16 07:28:50.912000',2,2,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Atlantic Marinols'),(217,'Atlantic Marinol GEN 4','atlantic-marinol-gen-4','[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"\\\"Zinc and Chlorine Free\\\" Engine Lubricant\",\"italic\":true}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"ATLANTIC MARINOL GEN 4 is a non-zinc and non-chlorine lubricant formulated with high-quality base stocks which provide low consumption characteristics, high-temperature oxidation resistance, and thermal stability.  These base stocks are combined with specially selected stable additives resulting in an engine oil with well-balanced properties.  ATLANTIC MARINOL GEN 4 meets the requirements of an SAE 40 grade marine diesel engine oil and is suitable wherever API CF and/or CF-2 performance is specified and is rated an LMOA Generation 4 lubricant.\"}]},{\"type\":\"heading\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Applications\"}],\"level\":2},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"ATLANTIC MARINOL GEN 4 has been specifically formulated to meet requirements of heavily loaded diesel engines manufactured by EMD and used in marine applications.  It is suitable for other marine diesel engines of the highest horsepower, or higher brake mean effective pressure (BMEP) using distillate fuels with a sulfur content up to 1.5 percent.  It will lubricate such engines in drilling rigs and stationary power generation service as well.\"}]},{\"type\":\"heading\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Properties\"}],\"level\":2},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"ATLANTIC MARINOL GEN 4 is produced with high-quality base stocks and selected additives. These provide the oil with excellent lubricating properties, low consumption characteristics, high-temperature oxidation resistance and thermal stability. Also suitable for other high horsepower marine diesel engines using distillate fuels with a sulphur content up to 1.5%.\"}]},{\"type\":\"heading\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Performance Features And Benefits\"}],\"level\":2},{\"type\":\"list\",\"format\":\"unordered\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"list-item\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Protects silver bearings.\"}]}]},{\"type\":\"list\",\"format\":\"unordered\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"list-item\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Excellent detergent properties at high temperatures.\"}]}]},{\"type\":\"list\",\"format\":\"unordered\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"list-item\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Good dispersant properties.\"}]}]},{\"type\":\"list\",\"format\":\"unordered\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"list-item\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Protects against sludge formation.\"}]}]},{\"type\":\"list\",\"format\":\"unordered\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"list-item\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Neutralizes acids produced in the combustion process.\"}]}]},{\"type\":\"list\",\"format\":\"unordered\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"list-item\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Zinc and Chlorine free.\"}]}]},{\"type\":\"list\",\"format\":\"unordered\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"list-item\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"High thermal and oxidation stability.\"}]}]},{\"type\":\"list\",\"format\":\"unordered\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"list-item\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Effective anti-wear and load carrying properties.\"}]}]},{\"type\":\"list\",\"format\":\"unordered\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"list-item\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"High TBN and Outstanding TBN Retention.\"}]}]},{\"type\":\"list\",\"format\":\"unordered\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"list-item\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Excellent water tolerance and separation.\"}]}]},{\"type\":\"list\",\"format\":\"unordered\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"list-item\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Controls carbon deposits and varnish formation, extending oil and filter life.\"}]}]},{\"type\":\"heading\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Recommendations / Specifications\"}],\"level\":2},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Meets or exceeds the quality requirements of the engines manufactured by Alco, Detroit Diesel (API CF-2) and Fairbanks Morse.\"}]}]','2025-05-16 07:37:14.722000','2025-05-16 07:37:17.384000','2025-05-16 07:37:17.374000',2,2,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Atlantic Marinol GEN 4'),(218,'Atlantic Marine Oil HD','atlantic-marine-oil-hd','[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"High Performance Mono-grade Marine Diesel Engine Oil\",\"italic\":true}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"ATLANTIC MARINE OIL HD series is a range high performance mono-grade marine diesel engine oils exhibiting increased dispersancy especially suitable for high BMEP medium and high speed diesel engines operating on distillate and MDO fuels.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"These advanced diesel lubricants are available in SAE 30, 40 & 50 grades to suit most marine engine viscosity requirements.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"The special balance of detergent and dispersant properties of these oils provide not only increased resistance to lacquer formation in severe service applications but also assist in sludge and deposit removal.\"}]},{\"type\":\"heading\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Applications\"}],\"level\":2},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"ATLANTIC MARINE OIL HD series are suitable for latest model diesel engines including those of MAN-B&W Alpha, Caterpillar (3600), Deutz and Stork Werkspoor. They have an FZG rating of 12 which makes them excellent extreme pressure gear lubricants.\"}]},{\"type\":\"list\",\"format\":\"unordered\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"list-item\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Suitable for lubrication of medium and high speed diesel engines used for fishing fleets and river transport applications.\"}]}]},{\"type\":\"list\",\"format\":\"unordered\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"list-item\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Main & auxiliary engines of all types and ratings, naturally aspirated, turbocharged or supercharged.\"}]}]},{\"type\":\"list\",\"format\":\"unordered\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"list-item\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Clutched reduction driver, reversing gear system, stern tubes and bearings.\"}]}]},{\"type\":\"heading\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Properties\"}],\"level\":2},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"ATLANTIC MARINE OIL HD series are designed for lubrication for use in high BMEP engines and in severe duty engine applications where the nature of the fuel and service requires a greater level of dispersancy and liner lacquer control than typically offered by the majority of diesel lubricants.  They are formulated from high quality base stocks along with a balanced additive system to ensure optimum performance and protection for trunk piston engines in marine & industrial applications where mono-grade oils are specified.\"}]},{\"type\":\"heading\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Product Benefits\"}],\"level\":2},{\"type\":\"list\",\"format\":\"unordered\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"list-item\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Extended Oil Drain Intervals.\"}]}]},{\"type\":\"list\",\"format\":\"unordered\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"list-item\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Extended Cylinder Overhauls.\"}]}]},{\"type\":\"list\",\"format\":\"unordered\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"list-item\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Reduced Bore Polishing.\"}]}]},{\"type\":\"list\",\"format\":\"unordered\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"list-item\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Superior Wear Protection.\"}]}]},{\"type\":\"list\",\"format\":\"unordered\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"list-item\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Reduced Oil Consumption.\"}]}]},{\"type\":\"list\",\"format\":\"unordered\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"list-item\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Reduced Liner Lacquering.\"}]}]},{\"type\":\"list\",\"format\":\"unordered\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"list-item\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Excellent capacity for water separation.\"}]}]},{\"type\":\"list\",\"format\":\"unordered\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"list-item\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Optimal TBN reserves.\"}]}]},{\"type\":\"list\",\"format\":\"unordered\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"list-item\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Increased oxidation and thermal stability.\"}]}]},{\"type\":\"list\",\"format\":\"unordered\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"list-item\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Improved Engine Cleanliness.\"}]}]},{\"type\":\"list\",\"format\":\"unordered\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"list-item\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Reduced Top Deck Sludge.\"}]}]},{\"type\":\"list\",\"format\":\"unordered\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"list-item\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Wide Engine Capability; Builder, Size, Speed.\"}]}]},{\"type\":\"list\",\"format\":\"unordered\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"list-item\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Reduced Piston Ring Groove Deposits.\"}]}]},{\"type\":\"list\",\"format\":\"unordered\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"list-item\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Outstanding protection against ring & linear wear.\"}]}]},{\"type\":\"list\",\"format\":\"unordered\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"list-item\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Excellent detergent and dispersant capabilities guaranteeing engine cleanliness & long life for engine & transmission systems.\"}]}]},{\"type\":\"heading\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Recommendations / Specifications\"}],\"level\":2},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"API service: CF, CD\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Meets or exceeds the quality requirements of the major Diesel engines builders.\"}]}]','2025-05-16 07:44:33.520000','2025-05-16 07:44:35.550000','2025-05-16 07:44:35.543000',2,2,NULL,NULL,'API CD, CF',NULL,'Atlantic Marine Oil HD'),(219,'Atlantic Marinol M','atlantic-marinol-m','[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Marine & Stationary Diesel Engine Oil - Medium-Speed\",\"italic\":true}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"ATLANTIC MARINOL M are Lower alkaline reserve (12 Base Number) trunk piston engine oil (TPEO) designed for use in medium-speed trunk piston engines burning distillate fuels with sulfur content up to 1.5% in marine or stationary service.\"}]},{\"type\":\"heading\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Applications\"}],\"level\":2},{\"type\":\"list\",\"format\":\"unordered\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"list-item\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Medium-speed trunk piston engines burning distillate fuels in marine main and auxiliary powerplant service.\"}]}]},{\"type\":\"list\",\"format\":\"unordered\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"list-item\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Medium-speed trunk piston engines burning distillate fuels in stationary powerplant service.\"}]}]},{\"type\":\"heading\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Product Benefits\"}],\"level\":2},{\"type\":\"list\",\"format\":\"unordered\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"list-item\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Engine Protection - Controls cylinder liner wear effectively and helps to protect bearings from corrosion. High performance, antiwear additives provide protection against wear for cams, camshaft and bearings. They also promote a high degree of water tolerance and anti-foam protection.\"}]}]},{\"type\":\"list\",\"format\":\"unordered\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"list-item\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Engine Cleanliness - Helps to ensure clean crankcases, piston interiors and lubricating oil lines.\"}]}]},{\"type\":\"list\",\"format\":\"unordered\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"list-item\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Easy Purification - Effective water and contaminants handling.\"}]}]},{\"type\":\"list\",\"format\":\"unordered\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"list-item\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Smooth Operation - Helps to provide minimum maintenance and downtime, long engine life and economical operating costs.\"}]}]},{\"type\":\"list\",\"format\":\"unordered\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"list-item\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Maintains power output - The detergent/dispersant additive system provides control of high temperature deposits in areas such as the undercrown of the piston and the piston ring belt area, enabling piston rings to function efficiently.\"}]}]},{\"type\":\"list\",\"format\":\"unordered\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"list-item\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Prolongs oil life - Base Number (BN) level and superior alkalinity retention characteristics maintain adequate BN to ensure corrosive acids formed by the combustion of fuel sulfur are effectively neutralized, thereby minimizing liner wear.\"}]}]},{\"type\":\"list\",\"format\":\"unordered\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"list-item\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Efficient purifying system performance - Excellent water separation characteristics enable water to be centrifuged out with essentially no loss of additive.\"}]}]},{\"type\":\"heading\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Recommendations/Specifications\"}],\"level\":2},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Meets or exceeds the quality requirements of the all major manufacturers for use in their medium-speed engines, including:\"}]},{\"type\":\"list\",\"format\":\"unordered\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"list-item\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"MAN Diesel & Turbo.\"}]}]},{\"type\":\"list\",\"format\":\"unordered\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"list-item\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Wärtsilä.\"}]}]}]','2025-05-16 09:18:32.694000','2025-05-16 09:18:34.733000','2025-05-16 09:18:34.724000',2,2,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Atlantic Marinol M'),(220,'Atlantic Marine Hydraulic Oil','atlantic-marine-hydraulic-oil','[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"ATLANTIC Hydraulic Oil HV Series oils are supreme performance anti-wear hydraulic oils engineered for wide temperature range applications.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"ATLANTIC Hydraulic HV Series Oils are formulated with high quality base oils and a carefully balanced super-stabilized additive system that helps neutralise the formation of corrosive materials. They are designed to work with systems operating under severe conditions where high levels of anti-wear and film strength protection are needed, yet they are formulated to work where non-anti-wear hydraulic oils are generally recommended.\"}]},{\"type\":\"heading\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Features And Benefits\"}],\"level\":2},{\"type\":\"list\",\"format\":\"unordered\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"list-item\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Exceptional Anti-Wear Protection.\"}]}]},{\"type\":\"list\",\"format\":\"unordered\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"list-item\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Outstanding Oxidation Stability.\"}]}]},{\"type\":\"list\",\"format\":\"unordered\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"list-item\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"High Viscosity Index.\"}]}]},{\"type\":\"list\",\"format\":\"unordered\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"list-item\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Excellent Corrosion Protection.\"}]}]},{\"type\":\"list\",\"format\":\"unordered\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"list-item\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Good Water Separation.\"}]}]},{\"type\":\"list\",\"format\":\"unordered\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"list-item\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Excellent Air Separation Characteristics.\"}]}]},{\"type\":\"heading\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Applications\"}],\"level\":2},{\"type\":\"list\",\"format\":\"unordered\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"list-item\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Hydraulic systems critical to deposit build-up such as sophisticated Numerically Controlled (NC) machines, particularly where close clearance servo-valves are used.\"}]}]},{\"type\":\"list\",\"format\":\"unordered\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"list-item\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Systems where cold start-up and high operating temperatures are typical.\"}]}]},{\"type\":\"list\",\"format\":\"unordered\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"list-item\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Where small amounts of water are unavoidable and this water could damage components.\"}]}]},{\"type\":\"list\",\"format\":\"unordered\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"list-item\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"In systems containing gears and bearings.\"}]}]},{\"type\":\"list\",\"format\":\"unordered\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"list-item\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Systems requiring a high degree of load-carrying capability and anti-wear protection.\"}]}]},{\"type\":\"list\",\"format\":\"unordered\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"list-item\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Machines employing a wide range of components using various metallurgy.\"}]}]},{\"type\":\"list\",\"format\":\"unordered\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"list-item\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Rotary screw compressors in natural gas service.\"}]}]},{\"type\":\"heading\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Recommendations/Specifications\"}],\"level\":2},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"DIN 51524 Part 2, Denison HF-0,HF-1,HF-2, Vickers 1-286-S.\"}]}]','2025-05-16 09:24:03.878000','2025-05-24 09:16:33.783000','2025-05-16 09:24:05.436000',2,4,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Atlantic Marine Hydraulic Oil'),(221,'Atlantic Marine Trunk Piston Engine Oil TPM','atlantic-marine-trunk-piston-engine-oil-tpm','[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Medium-Speed Trunk-Piston Diesel Engine Oil, VLSFO\",\"italic\":true}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"ATLANTIC MARINE TRUNK PISTON ENGINE OIL TPM series are trunk piston engine oil designed for use in medium speed diesel engines operating on distillate fuels and Very Low Sulphur Fuels (VLSFO)  having sulphur contents <0.5 % . The modern additive technology used in this oil provides superior engine cleanliness & protection. This oil is available in SAE 30 & SAE 40 viscosity grades with a BN (Base Number) of 12 to 20. These oils exhibit a high degree of water tolerance and meet the performance requirements of API CF.\"}]},{\"type\":\"heading\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Features And Benefits\"}],\"level\":2},{\"type\":\"list\",\"format\":\"unordered\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"list-item\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Superior detergency ensures piston and crankcase cleanliness.\"}]}]},{\"type\":\"list\",\"format\":\"unordered\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"list-item\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Improved anti-wear property minimises engine wear and reduces maintenance costs.\"}]}]},{\"type\":\"list\",\"format\":\"unordered\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"list-item\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Excellent thermo-oxidative stability retards oil degradation and controls its viscosity.\"}]}]},{\"type\":\"list\",\"format\":\"unordered\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"list-item\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Reserve BN ensures protection of engine parts against corrosive combustion products.\"}]}]},{\"type\":\"list\",\"format\":\"unordered\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"list-item\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Better demulsibility characteristics ensure water separation leading to trouble free operation.\"}]}]},{\"type\":\"list\",\"format\":\"unordered\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"list-item\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Special rust & corrosion inhibitors prevent corrosion of engine parts in severe salt water environment.\"}]}]},{\"type\":\"heading\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Applications\"}],\"level\":2},{\"type\":\"list\",\"format\":\"unordered\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"list-item\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Recommended for medium speed engines used in marine, power generation and industrial applications operating on distillate fuel, Very Low Sulphur Fuel (VLSFO) having sulphur contents <0.5% and Ultra Low Sulphur Fuel (ULSFO) having Sulphur content less than 0.1%. This product is also suitable for older engines where liner-lacquer is not a potential problem.\"}]}]},{\"type\":\"list\",\"format\":\"unordered\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"list-item\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Oils of appropriate BN to be chosen based on the sulphur content of fuel used. Follow manufacturers’ recommendation for selection of suitable BN level/ viscosity grade.\"}]}]},{\"type\":\"list\",\"format\":\"unordered\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"list-item\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Also recommended for general lubrication of shipboard equipment where specialised lubricants are not required or use of API CF quality oils are adequate.\"}]}]},{\"type\":\"heading\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Recommendations/Specifications\"}],\"level\":2},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"API service: exceeds CF specification\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Meets or exceeds the quality requirements of the all major medium speed engine manufacturers such as WÄRTSILÄ, MAN diesel, Caterpillar MaK, Yanmar, Daihatsu, MWM Deutz, SKL Motor, HiMSEN & Rolls Royce.\"}]}]','2025-05-16 09:30:19.722000','2025-05-24 09:15:47.279000','2025-05-16 09:30:21.656000',2,4,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Atlantic Marine Trunk Piston Engine Oil TPM'),(222,'Atlantic Marine Turbine Oil Syn','atlantic-marine-turbine-oil-syn','[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"ATLANTIC TUTBINE OIL SYN is a supreme performance, synthetic turbine oil designed specifically to meet the needs of the most severe marine and industrial gas turbine applications. It has a nominal 10,000 hour TOST life and is recommended for the lubrication of marine and land-based gas turbines, particularly units under 3,000 hp used as standby power units. This innovative product is formulated from wax-free synthesized hydrocarbons and a unique additive system. This formula provides outstanding low temperature fluiditiy and exceptional resistance to degradation at high temperatures well beyond the capabilities of premium quality mineral oils. Mobil SHC 824 lubricant also provides excellent antiwear properties as well as protection against rust and corrosion. It has good air release performance and resistance to foaming. \"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"ATLANTIC TURBINE OIL SYN provides superior resistance to thermal/oxidative degradation during the heat soaking period after shutdown and permits rapid oil circulation at low temperatures during start-up. Degradation resistance is a key attribute in avoiding harmful deposits that can interfere with lubrication supply to the bearings or foul critical servo-valves. This is a particular issue when gas turbines are running in cycling mode and experience multiple thermal stress cycles. Since low temperature fluidity and high viscosity index are inherent characteristics of this fluid, it does not change in service as a result of mechanical shearing or repeated cycling from low to high temperatures.\"}]},{\"type\":\"heading\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Features And Benefits\"}],\"level\":2},{\"type\":\"list\",\"format\":\"unordered\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"list-item\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Outstanding high thermal/oxidative stability and deposit control.\"}]}]},{\"type\":\"list\",\"format\":\"unordered\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"list-item\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Excellent low temperature fluidity.\"}]}]},{\"type\":\"list\",\"format\":\"unordered\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"list-item\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Naturally high Viscosity Index.\"}]}]},{\"type\":\"list\",\"format\":\"unordered\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"list-item\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Very good resistance to foaming and good air release.\"}]}]},{\"type\":\"list\",\"format\":\"unordered\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"list-item\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Excellent antiwear performance.\"}]}]},{\"type\":\"heading\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Applications\"}],\"level\":2},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"ATLANTIC TURBINE OIL SYN  is designed specifically to meet the needs of the most severe gas turbine applications. It is fully compatible with mineral oils, but admixture will detract from its superior performance properties. \"}]},{\"type\":\"heading\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Recommendations/Approvals\"}],\"level\":2},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Siemens TLV 9013 0, Meets Solar ES9-224 Class 1, Alstom HTGD 90117.\"}]}]','2025-05-16 09:38:24.001000','2025-05-21 05:53:37.183000','2025-05-16 09:38:26.301000',2,2,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Atlantic Marine Turbine Oil Syn'),(223,'Atlantic Marine Gear Oil EP','atlantic-marine-gear-oil-ep','[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"ATLANTIC GEAR OIL EP series are extra high performance gear oils having outstanding extreme pressure characteristics and load-carrying properties, intended for use in all types of enclosed gear drives with circulation or splash lubrication systems.\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"ATLANTIC GEAR OIL EP series is formulated to protect gear teeth from wear at its earliest stages. ATLANTIC GEAR OIL EP series oils are recommended for industrial spur, helical and bevel enclosed gears with circulation or splash lubrication, operating at bulk oil temperatures up to 100ºC. They are particularly suitable for gear sets working under heavy or shock loads. ATLANTIC GEAR OIL EP  oils also find broad application in marine gearing applications. They may also be used in non-gear applications include highly loaded and slow speed plain and rolling contact bearings.  \"}]},{\"type\":\"heading\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Applications\"}],\"level\":2},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"ATLANTIC GEAR OIL EP lubricants are used in a wide range of industrial and marine applications, especially spur, helical, bevel and worm gearing. Specific applications include:  \"}]},{\"type\":\"list\",\"format\":\"unordered\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"list-item\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Industrial gearing for conveyers, agitators, dryers, extruders, fans, mixers, presses, pulpers, pumps (including oil well pumps), screens, extruders and other heavy duty applications.\"}]}]},{\"type\":\"list\",\"format\":\"unordered\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"list-item\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Marine gearing including main propulsion, centrifuges, deck machinery such as winches, windlasses, cranes, turning gears, pumps, elevators and rudder carriers.\"}]}]},{\"type\":\"list\",\"format\":\"unordered\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"list-item\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Non-gear applications include shaft couplings, screws and heavily loaded plain and rolling contact bearings operating at slow speeds.\"}]}]},{\"type\":\"heading\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Features And Benefits\"}],\"level\":2},{\"type\":\"list\",\"format\":\"unordered\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"list-item\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Reduced debris denting from generated wear particles.\"}]}]},{\"type\":\"list\",\"format\":\"unordered\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"list-item\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Enhanced gear wear protection from micro pitting.\"}]}]},{\"type\":\"list\",\"format\":\"unordered\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"list-item\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Improved bearing wear protection.\"}]}]},{\"type\":\"list\",\"format\":\"unordered\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"list-item\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Excellent resistance to oil oxidation and thermal degradation.\"}]}]},{\"type\":\"list\",\"format\":\"unordered\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"list-item\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"High resistance to sludge and deposit formation.\"}]}]},{\"type\":\"list\",\"format\":\"unordered\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"list-item\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Optimized resistance to rust and corrosion of steel and corrosion of copper and soft metal alloys.\"}]}]},{\"type\":\"list\",\"format\":\"unordered\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"list-item\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Resistance to foaming and emulsion formation.\"}]}]},{\"type\":\"heading\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Recommendations/Specifications\"}],\"level\":2},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"AGMA 9005-E02, DIN 51517 Part 3 , ISO 12925-1 Type, Mueller Weingarten DT 55 005.\"}]}]','2025-05-16 09:44:14.455000','2025-05-26 12:03:15.195000','2025-05-16 09:44:16.166000',2,4,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Atlantic Marine Gear Oil EP'),(224,'Atlantic Marine Air Compressor Oil SPL','atlantic-marine-air-compressor-oil-spl','[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"ATLANTIC AIR COMPRESSOR OIL SPL is a premium performance ashless air compressor lubricant designed to meet the stringent requirements of major compressor manufacturers. It is formulated with high quality mineral base-oils and a high performance additive system designed to provide exceptional equipment protection and reliability for modern compressors operating under mild to severe conditions in marine and industrial applications. It provides excellent wear protection and the ability to reduce maintenance costs by minimizing downstream deposits and carryover. \"}]},{\"type\":\"heading\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Applications\"}],\"level\":2},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"ATLANTIC AIR COMPRESSOR OIL SPL is recommended for single and multistage air compressors in marine and industrial applications. It is particularly effective for continuous high temperature operation with discharge temperatures up to 150ºC. It is suitable for reciprocating air compressor crankcases and cylinders. It is recommended for units with a history of excess oil degradation, poor valve performance or deposit formation. It is compatible with all metals used in modern compressor construction and with mineral-oil compatible elastomers used in seals, O-rings and gaskets.\"}]},{\"type\":\"heading\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Performance Features And Benefits\"}],\"level\":2},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Low ash and carbon formation, Outstanding oxidation and thermal stability High load-carrying ability Excellent water separability, Effective rust and corrosion protection.\"}]},{\"type\":\"heading\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Recommendations/Specifications\"}],\"level\":2},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"ISO 6743-3A DAA NORMAL DUTY.\"}]}]','2025-05-16 09:47:57.789000','2025-05-16 09:47:59.829000','2025-05-16 09:47:59.813000',2,2,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Atlantic Marine Air Compressor Oil SPL'),(225,'Atlantic Marine Refrigration Compressor Oils SYN','atlantic-marine-refrigration-compressor-oils-syn','[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"ATLANTIC MARINE REFRIGATION COMPRESSOR OIL series are fully synthetic, supreme performance lubricants, specifically designed for use in refrigeration compressors and heat pumps used in marine, commercial and industrial applications. They are formulated from wax-free, synthesized hydrocarbon polyalphaolefin (PAO) fluids, which have outstanding resistance to thermal/oxidative degradation. With their naturally high shear stable viscosity index and low temperature fluidity, they are able to perform in severe service conditions that are beyond the capabilities of conventional mineral oils. Their solubility and miscibility with refrigerants is low, resulting in higher film thickness in the presence of refrigerants under pressure and reduced shaft seal leakage. Their stability and low volatility eliminates \\\"light end stripping\\\" which can occur with conventional mineral oils. ATLANTIC MARINE REFRIGATION COMPRESSOR OIL series help reduce frictional losses and improve machine operating efficiency.  \"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"ATLANTIC MARINE REFRIGATION COMPRESSOR lubricants are ideal for refrigeration compressors that operate under extremely high temperatures and for systems with very low evaporator temperatures. They are compatible with compressor systems utilizing refrigerants like ammonia, carbon dioxide, and HCFCs such as R-22. Additionally, they have proven to perform well with CFC refrigerants like R-12. They are compatible with all refrigerants except sulfur dioxide and have shown particular effectiveness in systems using ammonia. While they are fully miscible with standard mineral oils, mixing them with mineral oils may compromise the superior performance characteristics of the synthetic lubricant.\"}]},{\"type\":\"heading\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Applications\"}],\"level\":2},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"ATLANTIC MARINE REFRIGATION COMPRESSOR OIL series are fully synthetic lubricants specifically designed for use in refrigeration compressors and heat pumps. They are recommended for use with the following refrigerants: Ammonia, R-22 and other HCFCs, and Carbon Dioxide They are compressor lubricants are designed for refrigeration systems with very high reciprocating compressor temperatures. In the case of R22 refrigerants, guidance from the supplier of the refrigeration unit must always be sought to ensure installation operation is suitable for efficient separation of the oil and refrigerant. They are also suitable for very low evaporator temperatures and for screw compressor systems using refrigerants such as R12.\"}]},{\"type\":\"heading\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Features And Benefits\"}],\"level\":2},{\"type\":\"list\",\"format\":\"unordered\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"list-item\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"High oil film thickness in the presence of refrigerant.\"}]}]},{\"type\":\"list\",\"format\":\"unordered\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"list-item\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Excellent thermal/oxidative and chemical stability.\"}]}]},{\"type\":\"list\",\"format\":\"unordered\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"list-item\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Low volatility.\"}]}]},{\"type\":\"list\",\"format\":\"unordered\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"list-item\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"High Viscosity Index and wax-free.\"}]}]},{\"type\":\"list\",\"format\":\"unordered\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"list-item\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Low traction coefficient.\"}]}]},{\"type\":\"list\",\"format\":\"unordered\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"list-item\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Seal compatibility.\"}]}]},{\"type\":\"heading\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Recommendations/Specifications\"}],\"level\":2},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"USDA H1 Quality Level.\"}]}]','2025-05-16 09:51:44.641000','2025-05-16 09:51:46.238000','2025-05-16 09:51:46.225000',2,2,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Atlantic Marine Refrigration Compressor Oils SYN'),(226,'Atlantic Marine Grease EP 2','atlantic-marine-grease-ep-2','[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"ATLANTIC MARINE GREASE EP 2 is a high performance, general-purpose industrial-type grease. This lithium hydroxystearate based grease is formulated to provide extra protection against wear, rusting and water washout. It is NLGI Grade 2 with a base oil viscosity of ISO VG 150. \"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"ATLANTIC MARINE GREASE EP 2 grease is recommended for most types of marine and industrial applications including heavy-duty applications where high unit pressures or shock loads are present. This grease provides excellent protection against rust and corrosion and resists water wash-out which makes it particularly suitable for equipment where moist or wet conditions are common. ATLANTIC MARINE GREASE EP 2 is general-purpose grease and is not normally recommended for use in centralised grease systems. \"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"The recommended operating temperature range is from -20ºC to 130ºC, but it may be used at higher temperatures if the lubrication frequency is increased accordingly.\"}]},{\"type\":\"heading\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Applications\"}],\"level\":2},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"ATLANTIC MARINE GREASE EP 2 is recommended for multipurpose use in normal to heavy-duty marine applications, including the lubrication of anti-friction and plain bearings, bushings and pins under normal operating conditions. It is particularly recommended where loads are high, shock loads are present, or where severe vibration is a problem. ATLANTIC MARINE GREASE EP 2 is suitable for the lubrication of flexible couplings. It is capable of lubricating bearings at ambient temperatures ranging from -20ºC to 130ºC. For continuous service at temperatures above 95ºC, proper purging and relubrication frequencies are critical for maintenance of correct bearing protection.  \"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"The good water tolerance and rust and corrosion protection of ATLANTIC MARINE GREASE EP 2 make it particularly suited for wet applications commonly found in marine environments.\"}]},{\"type\":\"heading\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Performance Features And Benefits\"}],\"level\":2},{\"type\":\"list\",\"format\":\"unordered\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"list-item\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Very good resistance to thermal, oxidative and structural degradation.\"}]}]},{\"type\":\"list\",\"format\":\"unordered\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"list-item\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Excellent resistance to water washout.\"}]}]},{\"type\":\"list\",\"format\":\"unordered\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"list-item\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Excellent rust and corrosion resistance spray-off.\"}]}]},{\"type\":\"list\",\"format\":\"unordered\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"list-item\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Very good antiwear and EP performance.\"}]}]},{\"type\":\"list\",\"format\":\"unordered\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"list-item\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Broad multipurpose application.\"}]}]}]','2025-05-16 09:57:07.286000','2025-05-16 09:57:09.739000','2025-05-16 09:57:09.732000',2,2,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Atlantic Marine Grease EP 2'),(227,'Atlantic Premium Plus 2-cycle Outboard Oil TC-W3','atlantic-premium-plus-2-cycle-outboard-oil-tc-w3','[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Superior Performance Two-Stroke Outboard Engine Oil\",\"bold\":true}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"ATLANTIC PREMIUM PLUS 2-CYCLE OUTBOARD OIL TC-W3 is a high-performance, two-stroke engine oil that is designed for many high-performance, water-cooled two-stroke engines used in outboard marine applications. It offers a clean engine and environmental performance. The combination of special base oils and additives guarantees long life. ATLANTIC PREMIUM PLUS 2-CYCLE OUTBOARD OIL TC-W3 can be used at up to a 1:50 fuel ratio, depending on the manufacturer’s recommendation.\"}]},{\"type\":\"heading\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Applications \",\"bold\":true}],\"level\":2},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"ATLANTIC PREMIUM PLUS 2-CYCLE OUTBOARD OIL TC-W3 is recommended for use in two-stroke engines manufactured by Johnson, Mercury, OMC, Evinrude, Mariner, Force, Mercruiser, Yamaha, Suzuki, Nissan, and Tohatsu or where NMMA TC-W, TC-WII, or TC-W3 oils are recommended. It is also suitable for use in light-to-moderate-duty, air-cooled two-stroke engines that are used in power mowers, chainsaws, leaf blowers, and lawn trimmers.\"}]},{\"type\":\"heading\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Properties\",\"bold\":true}],\"level\":2},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"ATLANTIC PREMIUM PLUS 2-CYCLE OUTBOARD OIL TC-W3 is formulated from highly purified conventional mineral oils and an ashless dispersant additive system, providing outstanding protection against exhaust port deposits, corrosion, and wear. Spark plug fouling and pre-ignition are also minimized, promoting flawless operation. The product is ideal for use in both modern and older two-stroke engine models.\"}]},{\"type\":\"heading\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Product Benefits \",\"bold\":true},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"   \"}],\"level\":2},{\"type\":\"list\",\"format\":\"unordered\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"list-item\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Non-toxic to marine life\"}]}]},{\"type\":\"list\",\"format\":\"unordered\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"list-item\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Excellent detergent properties at high temperatures\"}]}]},{\"type\":\"list