tal components\"}]}]},{\"type\":\"list\",\"format\":\"unordered\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"list-item\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Mobile and stationary hydraulic vane-, piston-, and gear-type pumps\"}]}]},{\"type\":\"heading\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"PROPERTIES\"}],\"level\":2},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"ATLANTIC LOW ASH HYDRAULIC OIL ZF is formulated with premium base oil technology and an ashless (“zincfree”) additive system that provides exceptional oxidation stability, water separability, foam suppression, and protection against wear, rust and corrosion. They are designed to meet or exceed the performance requirements of conventional antiwear hydraulic oils, especially in severe, high-output applications such as axial piston pumps. The antiwear performance of these oils makes them especially suited for high performance industrial applications utilizing axial piston pumps where pressures may exceed 5000 psi.\"}]},{\"type\":\"heading\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"PERFORMANCE FEATURES AND BENEFITS\"}],\"level\":2},{\"type\":\"list\",\"format\":\"unordered\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"list-item\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Long fluid life – maintenance saving\"}]}]},{\"type\":\"list\",\"format\":\"unordered\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"list-item\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Premium performance\"}]}]},{\"type\":\"list\",\"format\":\"unordered\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"list-item\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Outstanding wear protection\"}]}]},{\"type\":\"list\",\"format\":\"unordered\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"list-item\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Low toxicity\"}]}]},{\"type\":\"list\",\"format\":\"unordered\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"list-item\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Maintaining system efficiency\"}]}]},{\"type\":\"list\",\"format\":\"unordered\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"list-item\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Excellent low temperature pumpability\"}]}]},{\"type\":\"list\",\"format\":\"unordered\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"list-item\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Excellent antiwear properties\"}]}]},{\"type\":\"list\",\"format\":\"unordered\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"list-item\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Zinc-free/Ashless\"}]}]},{\"type\":\"list\",\"format\":\"unordered\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"list-item\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Exceptional oxidation stability\"}]}]},{\"type\":\"heading\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"RECOMMENDATIONS / SPECIFICATIONS\"}],\"level\":2},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"DENISON HF-0, HF-1, HF-2, CINCINNATI MILACRON P-68(ISO 32), P-70(ISO 46), P-69(ISO 68), ASTM D6158 HM (ISO 32, 46, 68), HV (ISO 22, 100), Eaton-Vickers for use in M-2950-S (mobile) and I-286-S (stationary) hydraulic systems, DIN 51524-2 (ISO 32, 46, 68), DIN 51524-3 (ISO 22, 100), ISO 11158 (HM fluids)\"}]}]','2025-05-24 09:04:28.354000','2025-05-26 11:56:31.728000','2025-05-24 09:04:56.454000',2,4,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'ATLANTIC LOW ASH HYDRAULIC OIL ZF'),(232,'Anti-Wear Hydraulic Fluid','anti-wear-hydraulic-fluid','[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"(Anti-Wear Hydraulic Fluid)\",\"bold\":true,\"italic\":true}]},{\"type\":\"heading\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"DESCRIPTION\"}],\"level\":2},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"ATLANTIC PREMIUM HYDRAULIC OILS G II are formulated with premium group II base oils and anti-wear additives, and are designed to give robust protection to hydraulic pumps in mobile and stationary systems. The use of premium base stocks helps resist oil thickening and deposit formation in service, minimizing the possibility of an unscheduled change of hydraulic fluid. Oxidation test life is higher than solvent extracted hydraulic oil products.\"}]},{\"type\":\"heading\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"APPLICATIONS\"}],\"level\":2},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"ATLANTIC PREMIUM HYDRAULIC OILS G II is recommended for most types of hydraulic systems, moderately loaded gears and bearing lubricated by circulation bath and ring oiling. It is available in a wide range of viscosities to meet a variety of design and operating requirements of hydraulic\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"systems of construction, agricultural, industrial, marine and machinery tools equipment fitted with gear, vane or piston pumps.\"}]},{\"type\":\"heading\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"PROPERTIES\"}],\"level\":2},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"ATLANTIC PREMIUM HYDRAULIC OILS G II is formulated with rust and oxidation inhibitors combined with premium base oils which help to prevent the production of abrasive particles from rust formation, and deposits, varnishes and sludges from oil breakdown, which can damage equipment surfaces and seals, and block filters prematurely. Robust anti-wear additive package minimizes wear by protecting surfaces when load causes breakdown of the lubricant film. Good hydrolytic stability and water separation characteristics promote excellent filterability in the presence of water contamination. Good anti-foam and air release properties help ensure smooth operation and system efficiency.\"}]},{\"type\":\"heading\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"PERFORMANCE FEATURES AND BENEFITS\"}],\"level\":2},{\"type\":\"list\",\"format\":\"unordered\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"list-item\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Excellent oxidation resistance under the most severe working conditions provides long oil life\"}]}]},{\"type\":\"list\",\"format\":\"unordered\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"list-item\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Load carrying and anti-wear properties protect pumps and other moving parts\"}]}]},{\"type\":\"list\",\"format\":\"unordered\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"list-item\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Superior protection against corrosion and rust\"}]}]},{\"type\":\"list\",\"format\":\"unordered\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"list-item\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Excellent resistance to foaming and air entrainment\"}]}]},{\"type\":\"list\",\"format\":\"unordered\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"list-item\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Compatible with normal hydraulic sealing materials\"}]}]},{\"type\":\"list\",\"format\":\"unordered\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"list-item\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Excellent filterability\"}]}]},{\"type\":\"list\",\"format\":\"unordered\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"list-item\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Excellent hydrolytic stability means minimal degradation from contact with water and good water separation characteristics\"}]}]},{\"type\":\"heading\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"RECOMMENDATIONS / SPECIFICATIONS\"}],\"level\":2},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Parker Hannifin DENISON HF-0, HF-1, HF-2(ISO 32, 46, 68), DIN 51524-2 HLP (ISO 32, 46, 68, 100),\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"ISO 11158 HM & HV fluids (ISO 32, 46, 68, 100), ASTM D6158 HM (ISO 32, 46, 68, 100),\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"CINCINNATI MILACRON P-68(ISO 32), P-70(ISO 46), P-69(ISO 68),\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Eaton Brochure 03-401-2010 (ISO 32, 46, 68), Eaton E-FDGN-TB002-E (ISO 32, 46, 68)\"}]}]','2025-05-24 09:12:56.465000','2025-05-30 10:32:57.763000','2025-05-24 09:12:59.362000',2,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'ATLANTIC PREMIUM HYDRAULIC OIL GP II VG');
